title: corn macaroni bake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk over low heat and stir until thickened. Set aside to cool.
Combine shortening, sugar and margarine and beat on high for 4 minutes until creamy.
Add cooled flour and milk mixture and beat all together another 4 minutes with a little vanilla, if desired.
Can add any food color.

title: nothing cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well. Blend in pineapple.
Bake in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: circassian chicken
directions: Grind nuts in blender.
Heat broth; add nuts and bread crumbs. Bring to a boil and cook, stirring until mixture has thickened. Arrange chicken over a bed of rice.
Pour nut sauce over chicken. Mix oil and paprika until it becomes red.
Dribble over sauce to decorate.
May be served cold.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until thick and add the beets and oleo.
Let stand in syrup 30 minutes before serving.

title: yummy squash soup
directions: Combine squash and onion in chicken broth. Cook until tender. In blender, combine 1/2 of the squash mixture with 1/2 of the cream cheese and puree. Repeat for the rest of squash and cream cheese.
Return mixture to pot and simmer for 15 minutes. Season to taste.

title: easy beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Fry hamburger and crumble up.
Put tomatoes in macaroni.
Put hamburger and onions in that.
Pour in baking dish. Top with cheese at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: the biltmore estate winery wine cooler
directions: Mix in large punch bowl.
Float a pretty ice ring in center.

title: french chocolate
directions: Blend chocolate pieces with syrup and water over low heat until chocolate is melted.
Add vanilla; pour into jar. Refrigerate until cool.
Beat cream at medium speed, adding chocolate gradually.
Refrigerate.
Scald milk.
Fill serving cups 1/2 full of chocolate mixture.
Fill with hot milk; blend.

title: italian biscuits
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, lemon rind and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder, sliced almonds and anise seed.
Spread dough out on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool. Cut diagonally and place on cookie sheet under broiler until brown.
Yield:
about 3 dozen.

title: stained glass jello(very good and colorful for holidays)
directions: Using 1 cup of boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water each, dissolve and make the three different flavors of jello; chill overnight.

title: oven omelette brunch
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Melt butter in oblong baking pan (13 1/2 x 9 x 2). Tilt bottom to coat with butter. In large bowl, beat eggs. Then add other ingredients. Bake 35 minutes until eggs are set (but moist).

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve each box of jello in one cup of boiling water. Divide each flavor in half.
In one part put 2 tablespoons of sour cream.
Put the clear flavor in an 8 x 8-inch pan first and let set.
Then add the sour cream into the other half and let set. Alternate the rest.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Saute chicken in butter; brown well on both sides.
Remove to warm platter.
Add chives to pan and stir.
Add wine and cook down.
Add cream.
Mix well.
Remove from heat.
Add mustard, blending well.
Return chicken to pan to heat.
Serve.

title: potato yeast rolls
directions: In a large bowl, pour one cup boiling water over oleo.
When nearly melted, add 1 cup warm water, sugar, salt and eggs.
Stir well.
Sprinkle yeast over mixture.
Let set a few minutes to dissolve.
Add mashed potatoes.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, beating with mixer.
Will have to mix the last 2 or 3 cups of flour with a spoon.
Put dough in refrigerator overnight.
Punch dough down several times until it gets cold.
Pinch off dough and form into rolls.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: classic gazpacho
directions: Cut 1 tomato, 1/2 cucumber into 1-inch pieces and transfer to processor.
Add red bell pepper and puree.
Transfer to bowl.

title: diet brownies
directions: Have a bowl empty.
Put brownie mix in bowl.
Crack egg in mix.
Pour in water.
Stir 75 strokes.
Put in oven for 27 minutes.
Take them out.
Let them cool.
Eat 'em.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in small bowl.
Mix cream cheese and oleo, then mix in powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold cream cheese mixture into pudding mixture.
Have ready 1 (16 ounce) package Oreo cookies crushed in a 7 ounce flower pot.
Place a plastic lid in the bottom.
Layer cookies and mixture into pot, starting with cookie crumbs and ending with cookie crumbs.

title: yummy cabbage salad
directions: Place cabbage and apples in large mixing bowl; add sugar, pineapple and marshmallows.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Just before serving, add nuts and vinegar, mixing gently.
Serve on crisp piece of lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in saucepan. Bring to rolling boil.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, oats, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let set until firm.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Melt 1/3 cup oleo.
Mix with 2 cups corn flakes and pour over top of potatoes.
(Oleo all together equals 2 sticks, melted.)
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar and peppers to a good boil for 5 minutes. Add Certo.
Boil one minute.
A little red food coloring may be added for color.
Pour into sterilized jelly jars.
Should make only half of recipe at a time.

title: arctic-cranberry salad
directions: Soften cheese and blend in mayonnaise and sugar.
Add nuts, cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and freeze.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: lobster casserole
directions: Melt butter, Mix with crackers. Line dish with 1\2 of crackers crumbs. Add lobster and can of soup. Cover with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350°, uncovered for 35 min.
Use of RITZ Crackers is recommended.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in a 350° oven until done (approximately 1 hour).
Scoop potato out of skin and mix with all ingredients except cheese.
Put back into skins and top with cheese.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: moist meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in a casserole dish 1 hour at 275°.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; break into small pieces.
Combine cornmeal, salt, sugar and soda.
Add milk and eggs; stir until well mixed.
Add garlic salt, onion, peppers, corn and bacon pieces.
Beat well for 1 minute.
Grease 10-inch iron skillet with bacon fat.
Pour 1/2 of cornmeal mixture into pan; top with half the cheese.
Spoon on remaining cornmeal mixture; top with remaining cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes. Yield: 8 servings.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Mix jello as directed using reserved pineapple juice as part of water; measure.
Mix pineapple with cheese spread.
Whip jello when it starts to set.
Whip the whipping cream.
Fold all together and put in refrigerator.
Add chopped nuts on top, if desired.
Chill until set.

title: vegetable creole(serves 4 to 6)
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan melt butter.
Add onion and green pepper. Simmer until softened.
Add cooked okra, tomatoes, corn and seasonings.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: black magic cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add eggs and liquids.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.
Cool and top with favorite frosting.

title: frosted meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1 can of soup, beef, breadcrumbs, egg, onion and salt.
Shape firmly into an 8 x 8-inch square pan, lightly greased.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Take out.
Frost with 4 cups mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes more.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt into a large bowl.
Measure milk into a 2-cup measure, add oil and egg and beat together with fork.
Mix well.
Make a well in the flour mixture, pour in milk mix.
Stir quickly with fork just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin cups (greased or paper lined) 2/3 full. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in 400° oven or until golden brown on top.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Heat milk and add marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat and add to remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put back into graham cracker box.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
In a saucepan mix Nestle Quik, butter and water and bring to a boil.
Pour this into the flour and sugar mixture.
In another bowl combine eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Bake in a shallow pan, greased and floured, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken and mix with remaining ingredients. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Place in pan. Pour Ragu over beef. Spread cheese on top. Mix Bisquick and milk until smooth. Pour over top. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Stir rice and seasonings into ground meat.
Mix well.
Form into balls, about 1 1/2 inches.
Heat tomato soup and water in skillet.
Put meatballs into skillet and cover tightly.
Simmer 50 minutes.

title: black bean soup
directions: Wash and sort beans thoroughly.
Place in large pot and cover with cold water.
Add sausage after cutting into 1-inch slices. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Saute vegetables in olive oil.
Add to beans; add bay leaf and basil.
Cook until beans are tender.
Remove 1 1/2 cups drained beans and place in blender with vinegar.
Blend until it forms a paste.
Add paste to soup with salt and pepper.
Serve over rice.

title: pineapple cherry ice cream
directions: In a bowl, dissolve sugar and gelatin in boiling water. Refrigerate for 1 hour or until cool.
Stir in the milk, cream, pineapple and lemon juice; mix well.
Fill cylinder of ice cream freezer two-thirds full; freeze according to manufacturer directions.
Refrigerate remaining mixture until ready to freeze. Yield:
3 quarts.

title: chocolate chip-banana bread
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in bananas.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; gradually add to creamed mixture until blended.
Stir in many marvels and walnuts.
Spoon batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.

title: wine-soaked cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add milk, melted margarine, sifted flour and baking powder.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° in small Bundt pan until brown.
Cool and remove from pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar with 1 1/4 cups water and boil until clear.
Pour over cake a little at a time, letting it sink in.
Before serving, may pour wine or rum over cake and serve with whipped cream.
Good also with fruit! Serves 8.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and take off bone.
Save chicken broth.
Cook spaghetti in broth; saute celery and onions until just crispy.
Mix chicken, onions, celery, soups, chestnuts and pimentos.
Put into large baking dish.
Put Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts and soups are bubbly.
Makes a large dish or two small dishes.
Can be frozen.

title: french chocolate mint pie
directions: Melt chocolate and set aside to cool.
Beat sugar and butter until smooth and add unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Continue beating and add chocolate and mint flavoring.
Spread into graham cracker crust.
Place in refrigerator for several hours.
Can top each slice with a dollop of whipped cream.
Rich, but delicious!

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix in bowl 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon of cinnamon.
Cut biscuits in 1/4.
Roll each piece in sugar and place in Bundt pan.
Mix 3/4 cup of sugar and 1 tablespoon of cinnamon; melt cube of butter and pour over sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Pour over biscuits in pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Then dump out.
Pick apart to eat.

title: make your own yogurt
directions: Combine the yogurt with the mint and garlic.
Stir in the cucumber slices.
Wash and dry the watercress.
Arrange each serving of cucumbers on a bed of watercress and garnish with the radish slices.
Serves 6.

title: cheesy chicken chowder
directions: In 4 quart saucepan, bring chicken broth to a boil.
Reduce heat, add potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Meanwhile, melt butter, add flour and mix well.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over low heat until slightly thickened.
Stir often.
Stir in cheese.
Cook until melted.
Add to broth along with chicken.
Cook and stir over low heat until heated through.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spray or grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix the rice and dry onion soup mix together and place in bottom of pan. Add 2 cans (your choice) cream soup over top of rice mixture. Place raw chicken over mix. Add salt and pepper and the 2 cups of water over all. Cover and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 2 1/2 hours. Uncover and bake 1/2 hour more to brown.

title: chicken and pecans
directions: Assemble this recipe the night before in order to give the chicken time to marinate.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat until fluffy egg whites.
Add sugar, egg yolks, cream, milk, whiskey and nutmeg.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, potato chips and almonds. Place in an oiled 7 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, then chips, then almonds.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Good either hot or cold.

title: pizza bubble bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle a greased 12 inch pizza pan with cornmeal.
Separate biscuits, cut each biscuit into four pieces placing in medium mixing bowl.
Add spaghetti sauce tossing to coat.
Arrange dough into a 8 inch circle on pan.
Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese and bake 15 minutes.

title: oven german potato salad
directions: In 2-quart shallow baking dish, combine potatoes, bacon and onion; set aside.
In small saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, mustard and salt.
Gradually add reserved drippings, water, lemon juice and vinegar.
Mix well.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened.
Pour over potatoes.
Let stand several hours to blend flavors; stir in celery.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: chicken-potato bake
directions: Place sliced chicken on bottom of casserole dish.
Layer potatoes over chicken.
Layer beans over potatoes.
Pour package dressing mixed in melted butter over top of casserole.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix and cook at 350° until brown. Makes 12 muffins.

title: 3 cheese lasagna
directions: Saute garlic, onion and mushrooms in olive oil.
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes (plus juice.)
Add spices.
Spray Pam in 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Place 1/8 of sauce in bottom of pan.
Put 3 uncooked noodles over sauce, then Ricotta, Mozzarella, sauce and Parmesan.
Repeat 2 more times, end with Parmesan.
Cover very tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: freezer ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in ice cream freezer and freeze until firm.

title: pineapple marshmallow dessert
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in milk.
Chill.
Mix crushed pineapple, sugar and vanilla.
Fold whipped cream and pineapple mixture into dissolved marshmallows.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: Put sugar, cocoa and milk into large heavy pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly after it starts to boil. Continue cooking until it reaches soft ball stage.
Check by dropping a teaspoon into cold water and rolling it into a ball. (Easier than it sounds.)
Remove from the heat when you can do this.
Add butter and vanilla; stir until thick.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch pan and cool.
May add drops of milk and reheat if it thickens too quickly.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips and butter.
Stir in 1 can Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and dash of salt. Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Makes 2 cups.
Great served over brownies and ice cream!

title: coconut crunch delight
directions: In a bowl combine first 5 ingredients.
Press into a lightly greased 13x9x2 baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Stir every 10 minutes to form course crumbs - cool - divide in half.
Press half into the same baking dish.
In a bowl beat pudding mix with milk.
Fold in whipped topping (or Cool Whip) and spoon over COOLED crust, top with crumb mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with strawberries if desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and beat together all ingredients except pecans.
After all ingredients have been beaten well, mix in pecans.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine the flour, butter and nuts until crumbly.
Pat mixture into bottom of an 8 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: one-dish meal
directions: Fry hamburger until browned.
Add onion, soup, water, peas and potatoes; stir gently.
Cover; cook slowly over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yield: 4 to 5 servings.

title: sour cream pecans
directions: Combine sour cream and sugar.
Cook over medium heat (240°) to almost hard ball stage. Turn off heat.
Add vanilla, baking soda and butter (or margarine).
Beat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add pecans, stirring to coat.
Turn onto lightly buttered baking sheet.
Cool and separate pecan halves.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Combine together and pour 1 cup chicken broth over mixture; put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with 1 to 2 cups corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix well the sugar, Jell-O and cornstarch.
Add boiling water and mix.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Cool.
Slice strawberries into pie shell and pour sauce over. Chill until set.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown the meat and onion.
Add the next 10 ingredients to skillet.
Simmer 1 hour.
Meanwhile, cook noodles as package directs.
Set aside.
Combine Ricotta cheese, egg, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Then alternate layers of noodles, Ricotta cheese, meat and Mozzarella cheese.
Make two layers.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes (uncovered).
Serve in 15 minutes. (Can be covered with waxed paper and microwaved on Roast for 15 minutes.
Brown under broiler.)

title: good rolls
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and eggs.
Cream well.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add to lukewarm milk. Pour into potato mixture.
Add flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead well.
Put in a greased bowl and let double in bulk.
Knead slightly.
Rub top with melted butter.
Place in casserole dish; cover tightly.
Place in refrigerator until ready to bake.
About 1 hour before baking, shape into rolls, cover and let double. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: grilled vegetable and ravioli salad
directions: Combine pasta, vegetables and salad greens in a medium bowl. Combine sauce, oil and vinegar in small bowl; mix will. Add sauce mixture to pasta mixture; toss well. Serve immediately.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Put rhubarb in unbaked pie shell.
Mix sugar, flour and milk. Add egg yolks and blend together well.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake in moderate 400° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In frying pan with oil, brown chopped onions and bell peppers. Add hamburger; stir until brown and drain. In large heavy pot, add everything and simmer 1 hour. (Add a little water if necessary.) Also good with noodles or rice. Freezes well.

title: chinese chicken with cashews
directions: Pour oil into large microwave cooking container with a cover. Combine all other ingredients, except cornstarch, broth, green pepper and cashews.
Heat oil, alone, for 1 minute.
Add chicken mix and cover and cook for 4 minutes, stirring twice.
Add green pepper and cashews.
Cover and cook for 6 minutes, stirring twice. Add cornstarch, mixed in broth, and cook 1 1/2 minutes longer, stirring twice.
Let stand, covered, 2 or more minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: caramel sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes on stove on medium heat until done, for 45 minutes.
Drain and add caramel, cinnamon and butter.
Blend in cuisinarte until smooth.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: flat cornbread
directions: Bring 8 cups water and salt to a boil in a large, heavy pot. Remove from heat; slowly stir in corn flours.
Stir vigorously until smooth; let cool.
Divide mixture into 3 equal portions. Transfer one portion to a bowl; work in 1/2 cup all-purpose flour and 1/4 cup water with hands.
Gather dough (it will be soft and sticky) and transfer to work surface coated with corn flour.
With palm of hand, lightly flatten each ball into a 10 1/2-inch circle, 1/2-inch thick.
Slide onto baking sheet; bake on bottom rack for 30 minutes at 475°.
Broil for 5 minutes; turn off heat and leave in oven until top has brown spots.
Repeat with other portions. Cut into wedges and serve with soft cheeses or bean dips.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and butter.
Blend on lowest speed of mixer.
Stir in nuts.
Measure 2 3/4 cups of dry mixture into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan; spread evenly.
To remaining mixture in bowl, add baking soda, cinnamon and salt and blend thoroughly.
Add sour cream, egg and vanilla; blend well.
Stir in apples.
Spoon onto crumb mixture, then spread gently.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cut in squares.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Yields 12 to 15 squares.

title: grann parker's chow chow
directions: Chop all vegetables and mix together with 1/2 cup salt.
I let it set about 2 hours, but can set overnight; drain.
Add spices to sugar and vinegar.

title: ruth horine's ranger cookies
directions: Cream margarine and 2 sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Slowly mix in the remaining ingredients.
Bake on greased pan, dropping by teaspoonful, at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: brownie cake
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix after each addition of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: auntie vail's italian sausage sandwich
directions: Fry sausage until brown.
Drain.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
If sauce gets too thick, thin with water.
Serve over French bread shaped sourdough rolls.

title: shoe string potatoes
directions: Mix butter, sugar, 7-Up together and pour over potatoes strips.
Cover baking dish with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Take out of oven; add nuts and raisins, and bake 15 more minutes.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Blend well. Store in tightly covered container.
This makes 3 3/4 cups of mix.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: In bowl, combine milk and water; set aside.
In skillet, saut onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and bouillon until blended.
Add pepper sauce and reserved milk; stir until thick.
Stir in cheeses until melted.
Serve warm with dippables.
Approximately 2 cups.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add ground beef, salt and pepper.
Heat, but do not brown.
In a 2-quart casserole, spread half of the cabbage.
Cover with meat mixture.
Top with remaining cabbage and pour soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into well greased 10 x 14 baking pan; bake 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut in squares.
Serves 10 to 14.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Put you chicken breasts in a bowl of egg whites for 1 min. each.
Put each breast individually in a large bowl of bread crumbs and shake and move around until chicken is completely covered with crumbs.
Lay the breasts on a non-stick or sprayed cooking sheet.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Take 1 breast at a time off sheet and put in pan with olive oil on medium heat.
Cook chicken for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on each side or until lightly brown.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Beat shortening at medium speed of an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to shortening mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition. Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool on wire racks.
Split cake layers in half horizontally to make 4 layers.
Spread Custard Filling between layers.
Spread Snow Peak Frosting on top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle top and sides of cake with coconut. Yield:
One 4-layer cake.

title: lemon mousse
directions: Chill milk in the freezer until there are slivers of ice in it; turn into a cold bowl and whip until stiff.
To the whipped milk, add lemon peel.
Add slowly, the juice of the lemons, beating all the time.
Continue beating while adding the sugar slowly.
Crush the crackers and cover the bottom of a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan with half of them.
Pour the whipped mixture into the pan.
Cover with the remaining crackers.
Cover pan or wrap and freeze in squares.

title: jelly roll meat loaf
directions: Using 2 pounds of hamburger and your favorite meat loaf ingredients (eggs, bread crumbs, seasonings, etc.), mix up the meat loaf.
On waxed paper, press meat loaf into a rectangle, 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Make Stove Top stuffing according to package directions.
Spread over meat.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over stuffing.
Using waxed paper to help you, roll into a jellyroll. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with Pam, seam side down. Pour and spread cream of chicken soup over the top.
Cover loosely with foil and bake for about 3 hours at 250° or 1 hour at 350° or until done.
The higher heat used, the more likely the top of the loaf could split.

title: fluffy peppermint pie(jello pie)
directions: Microwave margarine and marshmallows in large bowl on High for 1 minute, or until marshmallows are melted.
Add cereal; mix to coat well.
Press onto bottom and up sides of greased pie plate or 12 muffin cups.
Cool.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Mix everything except cheese together and put in baking dish. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: walk around chili
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic.
Add all spices.
Add tomatoes. Simmer until ingredients are well done.

title: ham rolls
directions: Melt margarine; add mustard, onion and poppy seed.
Spread on rolls, then add ham.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
(Cover tightly with foil.)

title: hamburger soup(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add carrots, soup and juice.
Simmer about 1 hour.

title: seattle clam chowder
directions: Brown bacon in large kettle (4 quart).
Drain off grease and set
bacon
aside.
In
same pan, combine water, bouillon, juice from
clams and vegetables.
Simmer until vegetables are tender. Add
mushroom
soup, milk, cheese and mushrooms.
Heat (do not bring to simmer) until cheese is melted.
Add bacon and season to taste.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Cream the shortening, the 2 sugars and vanilla.
Add the egg.
Mix together the dry and creamed mixtures and add the nuts, oatmeal and cut-up gumdrops.
Make into balls and put on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: steak teriyaki
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Marinate flank steak at least one hour in sauce.
Broil steak until medium rare.
Heat remaining sauce; pour over steak and serve.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta cheese, eggs, salt, pepper and 1/3 cup grated cheese.
Boil lasagna in 4 quarts of salted water to which a tablespoon of oil has been added.
(Oil keeps lasagna from sticking.)
Cook for 15 minutes, drain and let cool.

title: chewy coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Garnish with candied cherry halves, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, until edges of cookies are golden brown.
Remove from baking sheets immediately.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: honey mustard low-fat dressing
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 cup.

title: baked halibut or salmon
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, lemon juice, shredded cheese and onions. Spread over fish and bake at 300° to 350° for 40 minutes until golden brown.
Serve.

title: my favorite beef stroganoff
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Brown meat on both sides in the margarine.
Sprinkle onion over meat in skillet.
Pour undiluted soup over meat and onion and add caraway seed.
Cover with skillet lid and simmer for 2 hours over very low heat.
Just before serving, add mushrooms, sour cream and wine and stir to mix. Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves about 6 to 8.

title: marinated tuna and vegetables
directions: Steam carrots and cauliflower together in a basket 10 minutes. Add peas and cook 5 minutes more or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Combine cooked vegetables, celery and green onions in a medium bowl.
Add tuna, vinegar and oil.
Toss, cover and chill before serving.
Serves 2.

title: oatmeal pie(tastes like pecan pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell. Bake 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together; form loaf.

title: stake with rice
directions: Cover bottom of casserole dish with rice.
Top with steak. Mix water and mushroom soup.
Pour over steak and rice.
Top with dry onion soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in covered casserole.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cornstarch to boil (about 1 minute). Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Set pan in ice water to cool; add strawberries and refrigerate.
Just before serving, top with Cool Whip.

title: fruity gelatin dessert
directions: In blender, cream all of cottage cheese to the consistency of sour cream.
Mix gelatin according to package directions for dissolving.
Don't add second cup of water.
Set gelatin aside to cool.
Add sour cream to cottage cheese and mix well.
Add gelatin and sweetener (or sugar) and mix.
Fold in fruit.
Pour in large glass baking dish and put in refrigerator to chill.

title: pineapple-coconut chess pie
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla, stirring until blended.
Stir in margarine, coconut and pineapple; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until set.
Cover with aluminum foil after 40 minutes baking to prevent it from getting too brown.
Cool on wire rack.

title: black bean chili soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook in pressure cooker until tender, not too soft!
Puree 1/2 of beans to make a thick liquid.
Add puree to remainder of whole beans.
Brown onions to taste. Parboil carrots in small chunks.
Add the chicken broth and sherry to the beans.
Add all seasonings, again to taste.
Add carrots and corn to soup stock.
Store overnight.
The next day, reheat and simmer a bit.
Eat!

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine carrots, soup and cheese.
Pour into a casserole dish.
In a small bowl, combine cornflake crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle cornflake mixture over carrots.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: candy coated nuts
directions: Butter sides of heavy 1-quart saucepan.
In it, mix the sugars and sour cream.
Stir until sugars melt.
Cook to soft ball stage (236°).
Add vanilla.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Add nuts.
Stir until well coated.
Turn out on greased cookie sheet. Separate into individual pieces.
Makes 1 pound.

title: creamy hot chocolate
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and store in airtight container. (I keep mine in the freezer. You are going to need a very large container to mix this in.)
This can be stored in one large container or several smaller ones.
This will keep for a long time.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, butter and salt.
Simmer on stove stirring constantly until it gets a little thick.
Remove from heat and add popped corn until coated.
Shape into balls and store in air tight container.

title: chocolate waffles ala mode
directions: In a large bowl mix together the Bisquick and the cocoa powder.
Add the milk, oil and honey and beat until well blended. Fold in the crushed Oreo pieces.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, flour, cocoa and 1/2 cup water.
Add another cup of water, then add vanilla and a pinch of salt and pour over biscuits.

title: chess pies
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs.
Add milk and melted margarine.
Mix well.
Pour into 1 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350°
until set.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine everything together except 1/2 of noodles and sherry. Pour in greased casserole and pour sherry over mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
After removing from oven, place other noodles on top.
Serves 4.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Take Crisco and onion, saute.
Put shredded red cabbage in the pan.
Add vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper to total 1 cup. Stir in.
Cover and let cook slowly until tender.
Stir every so often.
Cook about 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: quick & easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in 2 1/2 qt bowl, add sugar, oil, salt and egg. Stir to dissolve sugar and salt. Stir in 1 c.
flour until smooth. Cover with cloth and place on rack over bowl of hot water; let rise 15 min.

title: tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Combine with other ingredients, saving half of the cheese for top.
Put in baking dish; bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Mix fruit juice and water well.
Add ginger ale and soda water.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Place in punch bowl and add sherbet when ready to serve.

title: baked onions
directions: Arrange onions in baking dish; melt butter.
Add honey and salt.
Pour butter mixture over onions.
Bake 45 minutes at 425°.

title: marble top meltaways
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and butterscotch chips; let stand 5 minutes and spread.

title: refrigerator yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast into sugar or honey and warm water (100°); set 10 minutes.
Add salt and half the flour.
Beat 75 strokes.
Add eggs and butter.
Add remaining flour 1/2 cup at a time.
Make dough into nice ball.
Butter bowl and place dough face down to coat top, then turn face up and cover tightly.
Place in refrigerator for 2 hours, then make into rolls (or roll dough into a 6-inch snake and knot)
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Keeps in refrigerator for 4 to 5 days.

title: potato wedges
directions: Combine dry ingredients and put in plastic bag.
Scrub potatoes and cut in wedges.
Melt margarine in 9-inch baking dish. Put wet potatoes in bag and shake.
Place coated potatoes in dish with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with sour cream.

title: christmas raspberry carousel
directions: You will also need 1 Jell-O mold.

title: ann landers' world famous meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Put into a loaf pan.
Cover with 2 strips of bacon, if you like that flavor.
Pour over all, 1 can of Hunt's tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: grandma carter's white fruitcake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add brandy, orange juice, melted butter and eggs.
Mix well.
Coat candied fruit, raisins and pecans with flour and add to other ingredients.
Add more orange juice if the mixture is too stiff.
Add flaked coconut. Coat mold with butter and flour.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours or until done.
After removing from pan, coat generously with brandy. Cut an apple in rings and place on top of cake after cooled. Wrap in cheesecloth and then in foil.
Put in refrigerator.
The apples will keep the cake moist, but they must be changed every 3 days.
People who do not like fruitcake generally like this one very much.
Serves 20.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Bake in 375° oven for 50 minutes.

title: salmon quiche
directions: Flake salmon.
In a bowl, blend together eggs, sour cream, mayo and reserved salmon liquid.
Stir in salmon, onion and cheese.
Spoon filling into crust.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: bucchinotti (italian cupcakes)
directions: You will need 1 package of cupcake tins.

title: lettuce layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces in a 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Layer next 5 ingredients in order given.
Spread mayonnaise over all evenly.
Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Garnish with cheese and bacon.
Chill 8 to 12 hours.

title: hamburger harvest
directions: Combine chuck, onions, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Pat into 1-inch layer in a 3-quart casserole.
On top, place in layers, potatoes, flour, corn, limas and then green pepper.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes; then sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes longer, or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grandma esther's brownies
directions: Combine.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hot pepper pecans
directions: Melt butter in a shallow pan.
Spread pecans evenly in one layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or just until nuts begin to brown.
Do not overcook!
Stir several times during baking.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over toasted pecans.
Mix well. Spread on paper towels to cool.
Store in jars with tight fitting lids.

title: oil free muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Mix the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix the milk, egg whites, and corn syrup together and blend with dry ingredients.
Line muffin pans with the baking cups, and fill with batter divided equally.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes.
Test for doneness with a toothpick.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Make three holes (like playing in sand).
In one hole place oil, in the second place vanilla and put vinegar in the third.
Pour 1 cup water over the top and stir.
Pour into 1 layer pan.
Make a second recipe for a layer cake or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 18 cupcakes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer first 7 ingredients together several hours or all day in crock-pot.
Brown beef in oil and add just before serving.

title: gold cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking powder and salt and sift together 3 times.
Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Beat egg yolks thoroughly until light colored and thick enough to fall from the beater in a heavy continuous stream.
Add to creamed mixture and beat until smooth, almost waxy in appearance.
Add flour alternately after each addition.
When all flour is added, beat thoroughly again.
Add lemon extract.
Bake in 3 greased 9-inch layer pans in moderate oven at 375° for about twenty minutes or until tops spring back.
Cool.
Frost with any icing you choose.

title: party mix
directions: Melt margarine.
Add the next 2 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add mixture to cereal and nuts.
Mix well.
Put mixture on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes; stir every 15 minutes.

title: drunken chicken
directions: Season chicken; dredge with flour.
Brown in oil and butter. Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
In skillet, cook onion until transparent; add parsley, tomatoes with juice, seasonings, sherry and raisins.
Cook uncovered 15 to 20 minutes (simmer).
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: shake mix for fish
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Store in a jar with a tight cover.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; brown in margarine.
Brown onion and pepper after removing chicken.
Crush bouillon cubes with fork. Add to onion and pepper.
Stir in rice.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 2 cups water.

title: toffee bars
directions: Three to five days before serving, preheat oven to 275°. Grease 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Into large bowl, measure all ingredients, except egg white and pecans.
With mixer at medium speed, beat ingredients until well mixed, occasionally scraping bowl; pat evenly into pan.
In cup with fork, beat egg white slightly; brush over top of dough and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake
1 hour and 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately cut into 50 bars and remove from pan to cool on wire racks.
Store in tightly covered container for at least 3 days before serving.

title: dot's mini burgers
directions: Mix ground beef, soup mix and egg.
Pat walnut size rolls of meat mixture into small burgers.
Slow fry until done.
Drain well.
Place on buns.
Garnish as desired with pickles, cheese, mustard and ketchup.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Add enough buttermilk to make a thick dough so it can be rolled out and cut with biscuit cutters.
Bake at 500° until golden brown.

title: apple rice
directions: Combine apples, orange juice, oleo, salt and cinnamon in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover, remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana chocolate cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs, one at a time, then bananas and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat until combined. Stir in oats and chocolate.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven 8 to 10 minutes.

title: beer roast
directions: Bake roast, uncovered, in 350° oven for about an hour, turning roast periodically.

title: microwave stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut the green peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and membranes. Set aside.
Mix the ground beef, tomato sauce, rice, egg, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Spoon into pepper halves.
Place on roasting rack. Cover loosely with waxed paper. Microwave on High until green peppers are tender, about 12 to 16 minutes.
If you do not have a carousel in your microwave, rearrange peppers after half the cooking time.
Top each green pepper with catsup during the last 2 minutes of cooking.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: In a large bowl, place salmon, removing all visible bones.
Add 1 egg, onion and 1/2 cup of cracker crumbs; mix well.
Add 1 egg, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs, lemon juice and seasoning, mixing well. Place remaining cup of cracker crumbs in a small bowl.
Shape salmon mixture into oblong shaped patty 1/2-inch thick; roll in cracker crumbs, coating each patty well.
Deep fry in shortening until golden brown.

title: chicken or turkey taco casserole
directions: Brown onion in a little margarine.
Add meat cubes and cook until tender, then add soup and tomatoes.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. In a large casserole, alternate layers of soup mixture with tortilla bits and shredded cheese, ended with soup and cheese on top layers.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350° until top layer is bubbly.

title: zucchini drop cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients, then add the next 5. Mix well. Stir in the optional ingredients. Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: caramel nut candy bars
directions: Lightly grease 8-inch square pan.
Combine caramels and milk in top of a double boiler and cook until caramels are melted, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and mix well.
Stir in powdered sugar and beat by hand until smooth.
Stir in peanuts. With buttered fingers, press mixture into pan.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours, until firm.
Cut into bars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until ice cubes are crushed.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
In 2-quart saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Blend in flour.
Add milk at once.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Add shredded cheese, salt and pepper.
Continue cooking and stirring until cheese melts. Remove from heat.
Spread 1/2 cheese sauce in bottom of a shallow 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Arrange potatoes and onions over cheese sauce.
Then make layers with potatoes and onions, topping with remaining cheese sauce, spreading evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: lazy woman salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix together or alternate layers.
For larger salad, double ingredients.

title: cabbage salad dressing
directions: Boil until clear, about one (1) minute.
Let cool.
Pour over 1 head (medium) cabbage which has been shredded.
Do not stir. Refrigerate overnight.
Stir before serving.

title: finger salad
directions: Spread crescent rolls flat on cookie sheet, 15 x 10-inch and bake as directed.
Allow to cool.
Cream first 3 ingredients together and spread on top of crust.
Sprinkle over top of this 3/4 cup of each vegetable you desire.
Suggestions:
cauliflower, onions, celery, carrots, broccoli, red and green peppers and others.
Top with 3/4 shredded yellow cheese.
Chill before serving.

title: maple bonbon frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients together until smooth.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Mix flour, pecans and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes in an oblong pan.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Put on cooled crust.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello, water, pineapple and pie filling.
Let chill overnight.
Mix the sour cream, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together and spread over jello.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: linda's squash supreme
directions: Cook squash and onions in melted butter until tender, then mash.
Mix mushroom soup and chicken.
Layer squash, onions, crushed crackers, chicken mixture and grated cheese. Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place 6 or 7 large sliced and diced apples in a greased 8 x 8- inch baking dish.
Mix together the preceding ingredients with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Pour 1/3 cup melted and cooled oleo over everything.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon cinnamon (more it you like).
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Cut bacon in half; wrap around a small handful of beans. Secure with toothpicks.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Place bundles in 9 x 13-inch baking dish; pour over sauce mix.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 more minutes.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute butter and onions in pan for 20 minutes.
Add beef broth and simmer until hot.
Ladle into bowls and top with croutons and shredded Mozzarella cheese.

title: cafe vienna
directions: Mix well in a blender.
Store mixture in airtight container. Place 2 1/2 to 3 teaspoons of mixture in a cup and add boiling water.
Stir well.
Makes 20 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: stuffed crescent rolls
directions: Separate rolls.
Place thin slice of cheese starting at wide end.
Mix together sausage, bread crumbs and 1 egg and 1 egg yolk. Save second egg white for the topping.
Place heaping teaspoon of mixture same as with cheese.
Roll to narrow end.
Place close together on lightly greased tin.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Dissolve Kool-Aid in cold water.
Add sugar and stir well.
Add pineapple juice and jello. Refrigerate.
Add 7-Up and sherbet just before serving.

title: jello salad
directions: Strain fruit cocktail well, saving 1 cup liquid.
Make the jello with 1 cup hot water and 1 cup juice.
Beat the cream cheese into jello.
Cool.
Add cocktail and about 40 minutes later, when it has jelled, add whipped cream.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix up both packages of jello and let cool. Add and fold in other ingredients.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: *If soup is used, use additional half can of milk.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, buttermilk sugar and eggs.
Swirl raisins, nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon into batter.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Test with toothpick.

title: fudge mallow candy
directions: Melt chocolate pieces with peanut butter in saucepan over low heat.
Stirring until smooth, fold in marshmallows.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: frosted salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water; add 7-Up.
Drain pineapple, saving juice for topping.
Fold pineapples, marshmallows and bananas into jello.
Pour into 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Add topping.
Chill overnight.

title: carrot cake sandwiches
directions: In small bowl, combine carrots, pecans, dates, yogurt and allspice.
Spread evenly on bread slices.
Cut each in half then in fourths. Garnish, if desired, with additional pecan halves. Place on damp cloth and refrigerate, covered, until serving time.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix cooked chicken and Italian dressing with hot macaroni.
Cool.
Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice and mustard. Stir in chopped onions, olives, cubes, celery, salt and pepper. Add to macaroni mixture.
Mix well.
Chill overnight in tight container.

title: hawaiian marinade sauce
directions: Combine and stir well.
Good as marinade for short ribs, thinly sliced pork chops or tenderloins.
Adjust quantity as needed for amount of meat.
Marinate meat overnight in mixture. Pour juice off meat.
Combine new mixture of ingredients; pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until meat is done.

title: rita's chicken and rice
directions: Season chicken pieces with lemon juice. Sprinkle liberally with soy sauce.
Add seasoned salt to taste. Cover and refrigerate 5 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: hot biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all together.
Add milk and shortening.
Roll dough out smooth, about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a biscuit cutter and place on a greased cookie sheet or pan. Makes 12 biscuits.
Cook 12 minutes or until brown.

title: make the best bubble brew(child-approved)
directions: Blowing and chasing bubbles is great entertainment for all ages.
Here's the perfect recipe that will guarantee spectacular bubbles whether you blow them or wave your bubble maker like a wand.

title: coconut-pineapple pies
directions: Melt butter.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add cornmeal, sugar, pineapple and coconut.
Pour into unbaked crusts and bake for 40 minutes in oven set at 325°.

title: creole sauce
directions: Combine tomatoes, onion, salt, sugar and sweet basil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Mix flour and water.
Add to tomato mixture. Stir well.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over stuffed peppers.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix Hi-C, pineapple juice and tea.
Chill mixture and ginger ale.
Combine and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish. Cook squash and onion until tender; drain.
Layer half of the bread mixture and squash; top with remainder of bread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: stu's corned beef cheese ball
directions: Cut corn beef into small pieces and mix with cream cheese. Roll into a ball.

title: pastitsio
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add paprika, cinnamon, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes; set aside. Melt 1 stick margarine and add to cooked macaroni.
Put layer of macaroni in lasagna pan, then a layer of meat.
Then sprinkle with grated Parmesan and Romano cheese to lightly cover meat layer. Pour 1/2 cup melted margarine over cheese.
Make another layer of macaroni, meat and cheese as before.
Finish with a macaroni layer.
Pour beaten eggs over casserole.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve blue gelatin in 2 cups hot water; add 2 cups cold water.
Pour into large glass pan.
Chill until cold.

title: christmas-cake cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, combine dates, pineapple, cherries, almonds, Brazil nuts and sherry; mix well.
Let stand at room temperature 1 hour.
Stif flour with baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter, sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
With spoon, stir in flour mixture until well combined; stir in fruit mixture.
Refrigerate, covered, 6 hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Drop dough by level tablespoons 2 inches apart onto prepared cookie sheets.
If desired, decorate with bits of candied peel.
Bake on middle rack of oven, 14 minutes or just until golden brown.
Remove cookies to wire rack; cool completely.
Store cookies in airtight container.
(A slice of bread in container helps keep cookies moist.
Replace bread often, to prevent mold.) Makes about 5 to 6 dozen.

title: strawberry pretzel delight
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Mix in crushed pretzels. Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan for 10 minutes. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Pour in strawberries.
Put this in refrigerator until it starts to set.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Pour gelatin mixture over cream cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Put in blender and whip until thick. May need a couple of spoons of water added.

title: sandra's biscuits
directions: Mix all together on wax paper lightly sprinkled with Bisquick. Melt butter in bottom of pan.
Place Bisquick in pan.
Drizzle butter on top.
Bake at 375°.

title: chocolate oatmeal drops
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk in a saucepan.
Add oleo.
Boil one minute.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well.
(May have to add more oatmeal, if mixture is too thin.)
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: corn chip dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add salt, pepper, Velveeta cheese and chili con carne.
Heat.
Add taco sauce. Serve with any kind of corn chips, Doritos, tortillas, etc.
Keep warm while being served.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Place in glass dish with pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove and add cheese (grated) on top.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: ham and cheese delight
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add ham, eggs, cheese, bread crumbs, milk and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour in oblong baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife blade comes out clean. Serves 6.
Great for leftover holiday ham.

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Stir soda in milk.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Beat well. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or longer until done.

title: toffee crunch
directions: Arrange crackers on a cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 400°. Combine sugar and margarine.
Boil for 3 minutes. Pour over crackers.
Bake for 7 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chips on top.
When they are melted, spread around with a knife. Cool well and then break apart.

title: country apple cobbler
directions: In a large saucepan, combine 1 cup sugar, water, tapioca and cinnamon. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Remove from the heat; stir in the apples until coated. Pour into a greased 8-inch baking dish; set aside. In a small bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, salt and remaining sugar. Stir in butter and milk just until moistened. Fold in cheese and walnuts. Sprinkle over apple mixture. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until filling is bubbly. Serve with whipped topping, if desired. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: velvet ice cream
directions: Mash apricots well.
Pour sugar and lemon juice over apricots; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Place this mixture in the refrigerator or deep freeze until well chilled.
Pour into freezer can and stir in whipping cream until well mixed.
Fill can to the correct level with whole milk and stir.
Freeze according to your freezer directions.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve liquid.
Cut apples and bananas into juice and toss well.
Add rest of fruit.
Chill and serve.

title: aunt mary's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and cook over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: party ham rolls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Cut roll in half. Spread sauce over bottom half of rolls.
Sprinkle with ham and cheese. Cover with top half of rolls.
Cover and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. May be frozen and reheated.

title: appetizer microwave crab supremes
directions: Pick over crabmeat and remove any cartilage.
Place in 1-quart bowl and flake with fork.
Add celery, mustard, pickle relish, green onions and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Spread mixture on crackers or toast rounds.
Place 8 at a time on microproof plate lined with paper towels.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook on 70 (roast) 30 to 45 seconds or until hot.
Repeat with remaining canapes.
Makes 16 canapes.

title: crunch-top pear pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Gently mix pears with sugar, orange rind and orange juice.
Arrange in pie shell. Combine brown sugar, flour and spices.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle over pears.
Bake 45 minutes.
Partially cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form a ball (size of a grapefruit). Sprinkle leftover beef all over the ball.
Serve with veggies or crackers. Snack complete.

title: sugar-free custard
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes (30 minutes if not covered), then
40 minutes at 325°.

title: orange-cranberry liqueur
directions: Start this 5 to 6 weeks before you want to use it.
Chop cranberries coarsely.
Peel orange, using the thin orange part, no white.
Combine cranberries, orange peelings and vodka in a glass or plastic one gallon container.
Cover and let stand at room temperature for 3 to 4 weeks.
Strain into a clear container. Filter or siphon off clear liquid from cloudy liquid, if present.

title: daisy apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

title: pan coating
directions: Mix on low or whip until fluffy.
(Hand beater or blender.) Fills around four small Cool Whip containers.
Store on kitchen shelf.
Use any time a recipe says grease and flour a pan.
Bundt cakes come out of pan so pretty and brown.

title: libby's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix filling ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center of pie filling comes out clean.
Cool.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Boil water and sugar; cool.
Add pineapple juice.
Blend bananas and orange juice in a blender.
Combine mixture and freeze. When ready to serve practically thaw, then add ginger ale.

title: zucchini-tomato frittata(makes 4 servings; carb count: 10 grams)
directions: Or substitute cholesterol-free egg substitute to equal 6 large eggs.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Bring to a boil; then pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in kettle; boil 1 minute. Add vanilla.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and oatmeal. Spoon onto wax paper.

title: fat-free orange cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spray pan with Pam.
Bake at 350°.
Cool in pan before removing.

title: chicken reuben
directions: Lay chicken breast in baking pan.
Salt and pepper. Dash of garlic.
Cover with small can of drained sauerkraut.
Pour 1/2 bottle of thousand island dressing over chicken.
Bake covered 35 minutes at 350.
Uncover and top with Swiss cheese slices, bake another 10 minutes.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Bring milk and flour to boil and boil until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool in refrigerator until cold.
Cream sugar, butter and shortening together on high speed with mixer.
Add vanilla and cooled flour mixture.
Beat until smooth and fluffy.
(The longer it is beaten, the fluffier it gets.)
This will frost a large loaf cake.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Beat egg, then add sugar gradually.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; stir into egg mixture.
Add vanilla and apples. Bake in greased 8 or 9-inch pie pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: In a skillet, brown pork chops in oil and drain.
Stir in onion, pepper, broth, caraway seed and celery seed.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 45 to 50 minutes.
Add kraut and apple. Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until heated through before serving; sprinkle with bacon, if desired.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, milk and eggs.
Cook and drain broccoli and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour soup mixture over broccoli. Sprinkle shredded cheese over top of soup mixture.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in saucepan; add cracker crumbs.
Spread over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Combine rice and broth in 3 quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer on low for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add vegetables, chicken and parsley.
Heat thoroughly, stirring often.
Yields 4 servings.

title: broccoli salad ii
directions: In a medium bowl whisk mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar until smooth; set aside.
Mix together broccoli, bacon and onion. Pour dressing over salad and mix well. Refrigerate until chilled; serve.

title: pineapple cheese torte
directions: Combine all and pat into the bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spicy tropical jello mold
directions: Mix jello and spices in bowl.
Add boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add orange juice and cold water.
Let thicken slightly and beat in yogurt.
Let thicken again and stir in pineapple directly from can (do not drain).
Pour into mold.
When firm, unmold and garnish with sliced bananas.

title: brown sugar pecan pound cake
directions: Mix sugars and eggs together.
Add vanilla, margarine and oil. Add milk and flour alternately.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° about one hour or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar; stir in melted and cooled chocolate. Add eggs one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each egg.
Fold in 2 cups thawed Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell (I like chocolate). Chill until firm; can be frozen.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: campfire potatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Place in shallow baking dish brushed with butter. Add flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add cheese. Pour milk over cheese.
Top with frozen hash browns.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until hash browns are thawed. Stir. Return to oven, uncovered, and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: husband's delight
directions: First Layer:
Combine margarine, flour and pecans.
Press into 13 x 9-inch oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown. Do not overbake.
Let cool completely.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour over the rest of the ingredients.
Keeps 1 month.

title: ellen's carrot soup
directions: Brown and drain the ground meat.
Shred the raw carrots, chop the onion.
Combine all ingredients and simmer.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: To mix, have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add soft cream cheese and blend.
Add eggs, alternating with flour.
Blend in flavoring and bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
(Start out in a cold oven.)

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind all vegetables and add 1 tablespoon salt and let set one hour.
Drain and add vinegar, sugar, turmeric, mustard seed and boil 2 minutes, then add celery seed and boil 3 minutes more.
Add green food coloring if desired and red pepper, chopped, may be added if wanted.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Process 10 minutes. Makes about 4 quarts.

title: corn vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, heat soup and milk to boiling, stirring often. Stir in vegetables.
Return to boiling; cover.
Cook over low heat 20 minutes or until veggies are tender, stirring often.
Stir in cheese.
Heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease 1 pound coffee cans, but do not flour.
Fill 4 cans about 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Very good.

title: dilled green tomatoes
directions: Some people
prefer the crock dilled green tomatoes for their crisper
texture and sharper flavor; others prefer these dilled tomatoes.
Either
way,
they
take very little time to make.
You can
make
them
with
any variety;
just pick the tomatoes when they are small.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into plate.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Melt white chocolate in the microwave, stirring every 30 seconds.
Combine rest of ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour melted chocolate over mixture and stir well.

title: amanda bread
directions: Use less flour if part of flour is whole wheat.
Combine corn meal, water and salt, stirring to prevent lumps.
Boil.
Add molasses and oleo; cool.
Soften yeast in water.
Add 1 cup flour to corn meal mixture.
Stir in yeast.
Add flour to make soft dough; knead.
Let rise until double.
Punch down; shape into 2 loaves.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and mushrooms in patty shells
directions: Put cornstarch in 2-quart saucepan.
Add broth gradually.
Add cheese and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute.
Add chicken and shrimp.
Heat until hot.
Stir in chives, pimiento and broccoli last.
May make day ahead.
If in reheating mixture becomes runny, add more cornstarch.
Paprika for top.
Serves 8.

title: easy white bread
directions: Combine warm water with yeast until dissolved.
Combine with melted shortening.
Mix flour, milk, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Slowly add water and shortening mixture.
Knead in mixing bowl for 5 minutes.
Allow dough to rise to double its size, then punch down.
Place in bread pans and let rise to double its size. Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: surprise meringues
directions: Beat egg whites, vanilla, salt and cream of tartar until soft peaks form. Gradually add the sugar, beating until peaks are stiff. Fold in the chocolate chips and the nuts.
Cover cookie sheet with brown paper and drop mix by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake in a slow oven at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: baked german pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Whisk eggs until blended. Sift flour, measure and sift again with salt. Add flour mixture to beaten eggs in 4 additions, beating after each addition just until mixture is smooth. Add milk in 2 additions, beating slightly after each. Lightly beat in melted butter. Using 2 tablespoons softened butter, butter bottom and sides of a 9 or 10-inch heavy skillet. Pour batter into skillet and bake at 450° for 20 minutes. Slip onto a heated platter and serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: ice cream sandwich delight
directions: Line bottom of Pyrex dish with ice cream sandwiches. Crush malted milk balls; use half of these to spread over ice cream sandwiches. Mix other half with Cool Whip; spread over top of this. Freeze. When ready to serve, drizzle chocolate syrup over top.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Drain oranges, cut into small pieces.
Mix well.
Add cottage cheese and stir well.
Pour dry jello over mixture and stir well.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour into salad bowl and refrigerate.
Sets fast and is delicious with any meal.

title: what it is called butter beans with shrimp
directions: Mix flour and oil.
Brown.
Cook down with butter beans until tender.
Add salt and pepper.
On side smother onion and bell pepper. Add to butter beans.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Place a layer of crackers in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix pudding, using only 3 1/2 cups milk.
Blend in Cool Whip and spread 1/2 of mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers, remaining pudding, then a layer of crackers.
You should have 3 layers of crackers and 2 layers of pudding.

title: sante fe scrambled eggs
directions: In medium bowl, blend eggs and spices.
Stir in green pepper, onions and tomato.
Microwave at High for 3 1/2 to 5 minutes, or until the eggs are soft set, stirring 2 to 3 times during cooking. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover.
Let stand for 1 to 2 minutes or until the cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop onion and lettuce.
Toss with 2 ounces Cheddar cheese, Thousand Island or French dressing and hot sauce to taste.
Crunch and add 1/2 pound Doritos.
Slice and add 1 avocado.
Brown the hamburger.
Add kidney or Ranch Style beans and 1/8 teaspoon salt. Simmer for about 10 minutes.
When done, add to cold salad. Decorate top with Doritos, sprinkled around on top, sliced tomatoes and sliced avocado.

title: fried bean burritos
directions: 1. Brown the corn with the olive oil, do not burn or the corn will pop and make a mess.
Add the red pepper, onion, garlic and brown lightly. 2. Add the beans, jalapenos (if desired), lime juice, and spices.
Bring to a light simmer. 3. Warm large flour tortillas in a microwave.
While warm roll burritos on plate. Cover with sharp cheddar cheese and bake in oven or microwave to melt cheese.
Serve with chips and a cold Corona beer.

title: cinnamon nibbles
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix until creamy butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix in flour mixture.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape level tablespoonfuls of dough into balls; roll balls in combined nuts and cinnamon.
Arrange on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes.
Yields 30 cookies.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix.
Form patties.
Cook in 1/4 cup oil or in skillet sprayed with Pam.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add remaining ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake about 30 minutes.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Add sugar, flour and
cinnamon to apples.
Mix well and let stand until juice has
formed.
Put
in jars and cold pack for 30 minutes.

title: toasted garlic bread
directions: Mix garlic, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese in butter. Cut French bread into 6 (1-inch) slices.
Butter each slice of bread and place under broiler.
Toast each side until golden brown. Before taking out of broiler, sprinkle with Mozzarella mixture. When melted, take out and serve hot.

title: oatmeal pecan pie
directions: Blend all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until nice and brown.

title: orange angel food cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon colored and creamy.
Add sugar gradually, then add orange juice, flour and baking powder.
Beat whites until stiff and add to mixture.
Bake in an ungreased tube pan, starting with a cold oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Set oven at 350°.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Cook onions in small amount of water and drain.
Melt oleo and mix with cracker crumbs.
Press in pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese over crumbs.
Add onions.
Pour milk over this.
Add Parmesan cheese, then Cheddar cheese and top with cracker crumbs. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: banana fritters
directions: In a medium bowl sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Combine egg, milk, butter and baking powder.
Stir into dry ingredients. Peel the bananas.
Cut each one in half lengthwise.
Dip banana halves into the batter and then drop into deep fat preheated to 378°.
Fry until golden brown.
Serve with hot Cinnamon Sauce or pecan ice cream and whipped cream.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, Karo syrup, peanuts and salt.
Cook on High power for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Cook an additional 3 to 5 minutes on High until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend well and cook on High for 2 minutes.
Add baking soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto well-greased (oleo) cookie sheet and spread. Cool 1/2 hour.
Break into pieces.
Eat and enjoy.
Great Christmas or birthday gift!

title: mock steak
directions: Mix ground round, pork, soup mix, 2 tablespoons Worcestershire, stuffing and tomato juice.
Form into steak shape, 1 inch thick. Wrap 2 strips thick bacon at outer edge to resemble fat.
To broil: While broiling, brush with mixture of melted butter, 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce and catsup.
Broil 10 minutes each side.
Use a carrot strip to make a bone.

title: heart attack on a stick
directions: Cut bacon strips into fourths.
Wrap bacon around little smokies and secure them with toothpicks.
Place on large baking sheet.
Once cookie sheet is full, pour a generous amount of brown sugar over tops of little smokies.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown sugar is bubbling and bacon is fully cooked.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter sugar and eggs.
Add flavoring, then the dry ingredients alternately with the sour cream, mixing well after each addition of dry ingredients.
Chill and drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Mix ingredients except egg whites.
Beat egg whites separately until stiff.
Fold whites into mixture and pour in 9 x 13-inch glass cake dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes; check with knife to be sure it is done.

title: bean-burgers
directions: Brown meat and add the other ingredients.
Serve over buns. This is a recipe that you can add to.
Things to add are onions, cheese, hot peppers, olives, etc.
You just let your taste buds guide you.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add broccoli, rice, soup, water, milk and cheese.
Bake in greased casserole for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: texas brownies
directions: In large bowl, mix flour and sugar.
In saucepan, combine butter, shortening, coffee and cocoa.
Stir and heat to boiling. Pour boiling mixture over the flour and sugar; add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onions. Add to other ingredients and simmer 2 hours or until thoroughly done.

title: lois lablancs' macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil noodles with cooking oil; drain. Salt and pepper noodles. In casserole dish, combine noodles and other ingredients. Mix together carefully. Top dish with a thin layer of preferred cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in a pan.
Let bake until the center falls.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Mix margarine, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt at least at 3 different intervals.
Add alternately with milk.
Add flavoring. Roll 1 cup walnuts in dry flour, mix in batter.
Bake in three 9-inch cake pans. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk. Add ground beef along with remaining ingredients. Form two loaves. Top with ketchup, barbecue sauce or undiluted cream of mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Chop beef into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in 3/4 cup chopped pecans to garnish.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.
Keep refrigerated.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: In buttered casserole dish, layer 1/2 of macaroni, topped with 1/2 of flour and followed by 1/2 of Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.
Mix egg, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over layers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Top with dried bread crumbs.

title: ham and broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ham and cheese on top.
In separate bowl, beat eggs and milk together; add Bisquick and mix.
Pour over ingredients in pan. Bake at 350° (uncovered) for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cut in serving pieces and remove with spatula.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip is great with veggies, potatoes and inside hamburger patties.

title: savory sausage casserole
directions: Mix sausage with the rice, soup mix, dry onion and sliced celery.
Add the water with bouillon, soy sauce and toasted almonds.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: south of the border mason-dixon dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Heat chili in a saucepan over medium heat for 5 minutes (or microwave for 2 to 3 minutes). Press softened cream cheese into the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Pour heated chili over cream cheese and sprinkle grated cheese over top. Bake for approximately 20 minutes, until mixture is hot and bubbly. Remove from oven and top with chopped green onion tops. Serve immediately with tortilla chips.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into pieces.
Cook and drain.
Chop fine pepper, tomatoes, cucumber and onion.
Add salad dressing and Salad Supreme.
Mix all together and chill several hours.

title: no bake mini fruit cake
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Cool; crumble into a large bowl.
Add fruits, raisins, dates and pecans in the bowl.
Using hands, toss and mix well.
Combine applesauce and lemon juice.
Add to cake. Mix until combined. Pack into cups.
Place a cherry on top of each one.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: sheepherder stew
directions: Combine flour, meat, salt and pepper in plastic bag and shake to coat.
Empty the flour and meat in large pot and brown slowly in hot fat, turning often.
Add tomato sauce, garlic, water, onion, basil, beer, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 more hour or until tender.

title: orange chiffon cake
directions: Sift into mixing bowl the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Make a well and add in oil, egg yolks and rind and juice. Beat until smooth.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients with electric beater and pour into buttered and floured single layer cake pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: squirrel in sauerkraut with sausages
directions: Cut up the squirrel into serving size pieces.
Saute in margarine until browned.
In a large skillet, fry 6 bacon slices and brown sausage in the bacon fat.
Add sauerkraut, garlic, caraway seed and beer.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
