Remove skillet contents to a deep baking dish or casserole, bury the squirrel pieces in the sauerkraut and simmer for 1 hour, adding more beef if it cooks down too much.
This may also be kept covered during the cooking.

title: nashville eggnog
directions: Beat 1/3 cup of sugar into egg yolks.
Add salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 3 tablespoons sugar, beating to soft peaks.
Add to custard and mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix
in order given:
margarine,
sugar,
flour,
potato chips, nuts and vanilla.
Drop
by slightly rounded teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at
350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Watch them!
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar if desired, when cool.

title: home canned tomato soup
directions: Wash tomatoes.
Cut out all the greenish-whitish core.
Do not peel!
Cook and run through sieve or food processor.
Cook onions and celery; put them through sieve.
Mix vegetables and return to stove.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
When boiling, add butter and flour which have been rubbed together thoroughly.
Continue cooking a few minutes longer, until soup is slightly thickened. Stir often, so it doesn't stick or burn.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Process 10 minutes at 10 pounds pressure in pressure canner.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs good and mix rest of the ingredients together.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between the middle and the edge of filling comes out clean.

title: meat loaf pinwheel
directions: Combine meat, crumbs and 1/2 cheese, egg and salt.
Mix lightly.
Pat out meat to cover 12 x 10-inch of foil.
Combine cheese, rice and parsley.
Spread over meat and roll up, starting at narrow end.
Wrap securely.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Cut into 8 slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Bring all ingredients except half and half and roux to a boil. When broccoli is tender, add half and half; bring back to a boil, then thicken with roux.

title: strawberry jam(diet)
directions: Crush berries until a small amount of juice forms.
Place in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Remove from heat; add the sweetener and mix well.
Adjust sweetener to taste.
Pour into jars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: delora's surprise cookies
directions: Cream together eggs, sugars and shortening.
Mix together in another bowl the flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add to mixture, then stir in oatmeal, coconut and flavoring.
Add nuts. Mix well.

title: georgia pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, syrup and butter in 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil on high, stirring constantly until butter is melted.
Remove from stove and gradually add hot syrup to eggs; stir all the while.
Add pecans to mixture and cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bill's chili
directions: In a heavy skillet, combine meat, onion, and bell pepper. Cook meat until brown and vegetables are tender. Drain well on a paper towel.
Place in a large pan. Add salt, chili pow der and chili mix. Stir until well mixed.
Add tomato soup, sauce, tomatoes and water. Mix well again.
Add potato.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Serve over rice or spaghetti.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar and syrup and simmer.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer toast on top of syrup.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Beat and pour over toast.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: leftover turkey casserole
directions: Toss together lightly.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Pour mixture into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle chow mein noodles over the top of casserole.
Drizzle with the melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: saucy baked beans
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine pork and beans, onions, green peppers, brown sugar, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Top with bacon.
Bake uncovered in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chicken and ro-tel
directions: Mix prepared rice with chicken and Ro-Tel.
Simmer and serve. Serves 4.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a pan, combine sugar, Jell-O and cornstarch.
Add water and food coloring, then cook over low heat until thick.
Let cool. Line prebaked pie crust with strawberries and cover with glaze, then repeat.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours before serving.

title: mama's angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Cut Crisco in until fine crumbs.
Dissolve yeast into water.
Make hole in flour.
Add yeast mixture first, then buttermilk and mix together. Brush over with salad oil to keep from forming a crust.
Cover and put in fridge overnight.
Flour dough cloth and roll out a portion.
I use same dough for biscuits or for rolls, roll thinner, cut, dip in oleo and fold over in pan.

title: potato candy
directions: Combine potatoes, salt and vanilla in 2-quart mixing bowl. Sift confectioners sugar with potatoes, 1/2 cup at a time.
When mixture becomes stiff, knead.
Add more sugar, if needed.
Cover with a damp cloth.
Chill enough so to roll in a long roll.
Roll in nuts and slice.

title: chocolate cream dream cake
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler over hot water. Beat in cinnamon and hot water. Add the egg yolks one at a time, mixing until smooth. Cook about 5 minutes in the double boiler over hot water. Cool. It is important that the mixture be at room temperature for the next step.

title: fet kucha(lard doughnuts)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll dough and cut with doughnut cutter. Drop in hot lard for a few minutes until brown.
Roll in doughnut sugar while still hot.

title: special k fruit cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients (first 4 ingredients).
Place margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Beat well, add vanilla and eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix until combined.
Mix in coconut, nuts, raisins and Special K cereal.
Drop by spoon (teaspoon) onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° about 12 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Yields 6 dozen 2 1/2-inch diameter cookies.

title: cabbage patch stew and dumplings
directions: Cook ground beef.
Add onions, cabbage and celery.
Cook and stir until vegies are almost done.
Stir in tomatoes and beans (with liquid), water, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat.

title: fresh vegetable salad
directions: Toss with one large bottle Italian dressing mixed with one package dry Italian dressing mix.
Can prepare several hours ahead of time before serving.

title: baked chicken stew
directions: Mix broth, water, tapioca, salt and pepper. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into 13 x 9 baking dish. Cover and bake at 375° for 2 hours.

title: mulligatawny soup
directions: Put first 7 ingredients in a deep pan and cook slowly until brown.
Stir in 1/3 cup flour.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
I usually serve as is, but if desired, strain, reserving the liquid.
Pick out the bits of chicken and set aside. Rub the vegetables through a sieve.
Add the chicken and pureed vegetables to the soup.
Heat and adjust seasonings.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Chop and brown sausage; drain.
Add celery; cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients, except for green peppers.
Simmer 20 minutes, covered.
Add green peppers; cook 15 more minutes, covered.
Can serve over spaghetti.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, drain and place into a buttered dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and broccoli.
Spoon cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water. Add pie filling and 2 cups cold water. Pour into serving dish. Chill until firm. Combine cream cheese and sour cream. Blend with sugar. Spread over jello mixture evenly. Sprinkle with pecans. Chill.

title: snowy fruit balls
directions: In a food processor, grind prunes, dates, apricots, almonds and raisins to a coarse mixture.
Turn out mix into bowl.
Add orange juice and honey.
Stir until well combined.
Roll mix into 1-inch balls and roll in coconut.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: winter soup
directions: Combine all ingredients with enough water to make a good thick soup.
Let simmer as long as you like.

title: easy, easy fruit pie
directions: Place stick of butter in deep dish and melt in a 325° oven, then let cool.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour this over cooled butter.
Place fresh or frozen fruit or berries onto batter. Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over top.
Bake 40 minutes.
Batter will rise to top of pie and brown.

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients. Pour in cake pan.
Sprinkle the chips on top of mixture. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Mix all together and let blend overnight.
Use with vegetables for dip or follow out pumpernickel round loaf of bread; fill with dip.
Tear up bread you removed from center into dipping pieces. Very good.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, except potato chips.
Put mixture in greased baking dish.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Roll half the pasty onto floured surface into circle a little larger than inverted pie plate. Gently put pastry into pan.
Combine cornstarch, Equal|, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Sprinkle over apples in a large bowl and toss.
Place apple mixture into pie crust.
Roll other half pastry into circle large enough to cover pie.
Cut out shapes from pastry using cookie cutter.
Place pastry on pie.
Trim and seal edges by pressing with fork.
Place cut out shapes onto pie crust. Bake 40-50 minutes, until pastry is brown and apples are tender. Cool on wire rack.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Thoroughly coat chicken pieces with flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Dust any remaining flour over chicken pieces in pan. Brown chicken in oil in heavy skillet about 15 minutes.
Add onion.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water; add 1/2 to chicken in pan (add more as needed).
Cover and simmer over low heat 30 to 40 minutes, or until tender.
Remove to serving platter.
Add remaining bouillon and sour cream (add 1/2 cup more sour cream if desired) to pan drippings.
Stir well.
Heat, but do not boil. Pour over chicken.

title: margaret's broccoli salad
directions: Combine salad ingredients and toss with dressing.

title: egg custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour 1/4 cup scalded milk into egg mixture.
Stir well.
Then slowly add rest of milk, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture into 9-inch deep dish pie crust shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake, as this makes custard watery.

title: stuffed pita scramble
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, heat margarine over medium heat until bubbly; add zucchini and onion and saute, stirring constantly, until zucchini is tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chicken and cook, stirring constantly until heated through, about 1 minute.
Add eggs and cook, stirring frequently, just until eggs are set, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in cheese and cook until cheese melts.
Cut pita in half crosswise, forming 2 pockets.
Stuff each pocket with 1/8 of the egg mixture and 1 tomato slice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl except chicken and mix well.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour rice mixture over top of chicken and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Resift twice with soda.
Set aside. Cream butter and add sugar slowly beating constantly to cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Stir in sour cream.
Add flour mixture 1/2 cup at the time, beating well and constantly.
Stir in extract and turn batter into a well greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Use salt free shortening or fat for greasing pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake is done.
Place pan on rack to cool 5 minutes.
Loose cake around edges of pan and edge of tube with dull side of knife.
Turn cake onto rack to cool completely.
Serve plain.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in slightly salted water for about 5 minutes, until thick.
While on burner, add oleo, sharp cheese and egg with milk. Stir until cheese and butter are melted.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: french italian grandmother's garlic bread
directions: Slice bread the size you like and spread with butter; sprinkle with garlic powder.
Put on cookie sheet lined with foil and heat in oven.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar, salt and vinegar.
Cook in double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and when cool, add whipped cream.
Prepared mustard may be added to this dressing using less sugar or no sugar.
It is then suitable for meat and vegetable combinations.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Beat eggs until stiff but not dry.
Fold in sugar; add vanilla, corn flakes, nuts and coconut.
Drop by spoonfuls onto well-greased baking sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Remove immediately from pan.

title: low calorie fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, marshmallows, butter and salt in heavy 2 quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat to a boil.
Stir constantly (mixture will be bubbling all over top).
Boil and stir 5 minutes. Take off heat and stir in chocolate morsels until completely melted.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan and cool.
Cut into 30 pieces.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and make into patties.
Fry on low heat.

title: jelly roll
directions: In small bowl, beat eggs 5 minutes until very thick and lemon colored.
Pour eggs into larger bowl and add sugar gradually. Beat in sugar.
On low speed, blend in water and vanilla. Gradually add flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Pour into lined jelly roll pan with aluminum foil or waxed paper greased well, spreading batter into corners.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Loosen cake from edges of pan and invert on towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar, carefully remove foil.
Trim off stiff edges, if necessary.
While hot, roll cake and towel from narrow end.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes.
Unroll cake and remove towel; beat jelly with fork to soften.
Spread jelly on cake.
Spread thin layer of Cool Whip and carefully roll cake up. Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until partly done.
Peel and slice lengthwise, about 1/2 inch thick, and layer in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Core and slice apple and layer on sweet potatoes. Heat fruit juice to boil.
Combine starch and water; cook until thickened.
Add honey.
Pour over apples and sweet potatoes.
Top with wheat germ and chopped nuts.
Dust with cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and ham bake
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add other ingredients except cheese and ham.
Add half the grated cheese; mix well.
Put filling on ham slices and roll up.
Put rolls in pan and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, remove foil.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese; return to oven just until cheese melts.

title: beef in potato shells
directions: Bake potatoes at 475°.
When done, cut potatoes lengthwise in half.
Scoop out all but 1/4-inch shell.
Brush inside and outside of shell with melted butter.
Place shells, cut side up, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake, uncovered, until edges are brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook and stir ground beef in skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in tomatoes and seasoning mix.
Break up tomatoes.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes.
Spoon beef into shells. Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat just until cheese is melted.
Top with sour cream and onions.

title: the trawler's crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Serve with crackers.

title: beer rolls
directions: Mix and pour in greased muffin pan.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in tight jar.
Mix 2 heaping teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: grape juice float
directions: Combine grape juice, lemon juice and cider; sweeten to taste. Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Fill glasses about 3/4 and drop a scoop of orange sherbet on top.
Serve immediately.

title: pork shoulder with vegetables
directions: In large skillet, brown pork slices quickly on both sides. Spoon off excess fat.
Arrange cabbage and potatoes pinwheel fashion between pork slices.
Add carrots, bouillon, caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 25 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: in the pink salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill 4 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Blend all together.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix cheese and onion with mayonnaise. Layer 1/2 vegetables and 1/2 mayonnaise mixture, repeat. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Combine margarine and cracker crumbs for topping. Remove from oven, spread on topping and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl and mix well.
Pour marinade over shrimp; cover and let stand for 2 hours.
Grill shrimp at least 6 inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes per side.

title: barbecued burger beans
directions: Brown meat and add onion until clear.
Then combine all in a large pan and cook slowly until all ingredients are hot.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes; run through a colander.
Chop peppers and onions; crush spices.
Cook for 1 hour; pour into jars.
Pressure for 10 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.
May also be frozen.

title: caramel for rolls
directions: Heat and melt all together over medium heat.
Pour in bottom of pan.

title: cheesy broiled appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread 1 tablespoon cheese mixture per slice of bread. Broil 1 to 2 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed and bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean, approximately 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves or 1 Bundt pan and 1 loaf.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with crushed potato chips and sliced almonds (almonds are optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown and drain sausage or hamburger, onion and green pepper. Add sauces and cook for 5 minutes.
Layer twice in crock-pot: meat, noodles, cheese, pepperoni and mushrooms.
Cook on low until cheese melts, about 1 hour.

title: gooy cake
directions: Combine butter, 1 egg and cake mix together to form a powder like dough.
Press down in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Cream together cream cheese, 2 eggs and vanilla. Slowly blend in powdered sugar, all but about 3 tablespoons (leave to sprinkle on top).
When blended together, pour over dough.
Top with 1 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until it doesn't wiggle in the middle of pan.
Let cool, then sprinkle 3 tablespoons 10x powdered sugar on top.

title: spiced cranberry nut stuffing
directions: In a small bowl, stir together first 3 ingredients; set aside. In a 4-quart saucepan, in hot butter, cook celery until tender. Add cranberry sauce mixture and remaining ingredients.
Toss to mix well.
Spoon into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 cups or 16 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place sliced berries in pie shell.
In a saucepan, add the 1 cup water, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Cook over low heat until clear and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add the strawberry Jell-O.
Pour over strawberries in pie shell.
Chill, then top with whipped cream.

title: frosted lemon salad
directions: Blend yogurt and pudding.
Mix in bowl until smooth.
Stir in coconut and pineapple.
Spoon into 9 x 12-inch dish.
Freeze at least 4 hours until firm.
Remove from freezer 20 minutes before serving.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Make salad: lettuce, tomato, onion, olives and cheese.
Keep cold.
Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add taco mix and half drained kidney beans.
Mix well.
Break chips in bag into large pieces.
Put on salad.
Pour on dressing and toss well.
Mix in warm meat and beans just before serving.
Enjoy.

title: wild rice with mushrooms(serves 8 to 10)
directions: In a large saucepan, stir together the undrained black-eyed peas, water, sliced onion, sliced celery, diced bacon, chicken bouillon granules, garlic salt, pepper and bottled hot pepper sauce.
Bring mixture to boiling.
Stir in the uncooked rice. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until the rice is done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pork chops alla prego
directions: In large skillet, over medium heat, cook pork chops until well browned on both sides.
Remove from skillet; set aside.

title: baked beans with meat
directions: Brown onion, pepper and ground beef; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and simmer or bake in a moderate oven for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: sonny's pizza sauce
directions: In saucepan, add oil and garlic.
Heat until garlic browns. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and simmer about 2 hours.
Makes enough for four (16-ounce) pizzas.

title: banana cake
directions: Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes in an 8-inch square pan.

title: company chicken
directions: Simmer soups and milk to blend.
Combine water and seasonings; add to soup mixture.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or this recipe will make 2 (2-quart) casseroles.
Lay spaghetti, then pour blended liquids over.
Add tuna and almonds.
Swirl through spaghetti.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: ham logs
directions: Combine and mix well like meat loaf.
Shape into 8 to 10 logs.
Place in a greased flat casserole and cover with Raisin Sauce.

title: chicken paprikas(chicken with gravy and dumplings)
directions: Cut chicken into pieces; set aside.
Brown diced onion in frying pan with about 1/2 inch of oil in it.
Remove onion when slightly brown and put in large Dutch oven.
Add chicken pieces to the hot oil.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Brown chicken all over.
Sprinkle liberally with paprika. When chicken is browned, put with onion in Dutch oven.
Add water to cover chicken.
Let simmer on low heat until chicken is tender. Remove chicken to plate and set aside for serving.

title: pineapple fluff pie
directions: Over low heat, stirring constantly, melt marshmallows in milk until smooth.
Let cool.
Whip the cream until peaks.
Mix together milk mixture, whipped cream and pineapple.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Refrigerate until set.

title: reese's cups
directions: Melt butter; add graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and then peanut butter.
Mix well; put in pan (greased with butter).
Press it well.
Cover with melted chocolate when chocolate is cold. Slice in small pieces.

title: easy freezer biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Roll out and cut.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Place in plastic bag when frozen.
When ready to bake, place frozen biscuits on cookie sheet in a cold oven for 10 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: evelyn's kringles
directions: Add soda to sour cream and buttermilk.
Add sugar.
Sift rest of ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Knead a bit on board.
If too sticky, work in a bit more flour.
Shape and bake at 500° for 5 minutes.

title: lemon luscious pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Prepare pie crust according to package directions for unfilled one-crust pie using 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.

title: buttermilk coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, salt and cinnamon in large bowl.
Add brown sugar and salad oil.
Mix on medium speed with electric mixer until crumbly.
Take out 3/4 cup of this mixture for the topping and set aside.
To the remaining mixture, add soda, baking powder, egg and buttermilk.
Mix until smooth.
Spoon mixture into a buttered pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch) and sprinkle reserved topping evenly over top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until tests done.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm or room temperature.

title: fudge nougats
directions: Combine sugar, butter and Pet milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour milk mixture over chocolate mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: no-bake raisin bars
directions: In a large saucepan or microwave-safe bowl, heat marshmallows and butter over low heat until melted; mix well.
Stir in the cereal raisins, walnuts and cinnamon.
Pat into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: corn light bread
directions: Put sugar, salt, soda and baking powder in a bowl; add buttermilk.
Stir well.

Then add cornmeal and flour alternately. Melt margarine in an iron skillet or baking pan in a 350° oven. Pour mixture in a hot pan or skillet and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until light golden brown.
Best when margarine is melted on top while still hot.

title: mom parker's coconut pie
directions: Cook milk,
sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt in double boiler until
thick;
stir
often	and
cool.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and grated coconut.	Sprinkle top of coconut and chill before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mush shrimp with fork.
Add all ingredients and mix.
Chill and serve with Triscuits or most any crackers.

title: stewed fish italian style, garlic rice and mixed vegetables
directions: Wash cod; pat dry.
Season well overnight or for several hours. When you are ready to cook, saute chopped onions, tomatoes and garlic in small amount of oil until golden.
Stir in fish pieces, coating well with seasoning.
Brown well; pour on diluted tomato sauce.
Adjust seasoning, cover well and simmer over reduced heat for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Shake pan from time to time to keep fish from sticking.
Spoon sauce over to keep all the fish moist. Prepare rice according to directions on package.
Add fried garlic. Saute chopped onions and garlic and stir in mixed vegetables with a small amount of broth.
Stew, uncovered, until tender, about 10 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Beat together 4 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spinach rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Place baking dish in a larger pan surrounding baking dish.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: one dish chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Mix stuffing, water and margarine lightly. Spoon stuffing across center of 2-quart shallow baking dish, leaving space on both sides for chicken. Place chicken on each side. Mix soup, milk and parsley; pour over chicken. Cover and bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: angel food cake
directions: Read carefully before mixing.

title: 3 bean crock-pot casserole
directions: Drain all the beans.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Brown ground beef and saute onion.
Combine all ingredients in the crock-pot.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: sausage potato bake
directions: Slice sausage into bite size pieces.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Slice potatoes thinly.
Place on top of sausage.
Use as many potatoes as desired.
Add enough water to dish to just about cover sausage.
Cover dish with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Discard any remaining water in dish before storing leftovers in refrigerator.

title: quick and easy taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add taco mix.
Follow directions on package.
Cool; layer chips, shredded lettuce, meat, cheese, avocado slices, tomato and top with your favorite salad dressing.

title: classic green bean bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in green beans and 1/2 can French fried onions. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; stir.
Top with remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes.

title: santa claus salad
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin, salt and marshmallows in 2 cups hot water; chill until thickened.
Blend cheese, pineapple and mayonnaise; add to gelatin mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill until firm.
Dissolve cherry gelatin in 2 cups hot water; add remaining water.
Chill until thickened.
Spread over firm gelatin mixture; chill until firm.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt first 2 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Top with croutons simmered in 1 tablespoon butter and salt, or top with French fried onion rings.

title: low-fat mushroom soup
directions: Add mushrooms, onion, lemon juice, salt and pepper to chicken broth.
Bring to boil.
Cover; reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 20 minutes, or until mushrooms and onion are very soft.
Add cornstarch to the 3 cups skim milk; mix until no lumps remain. Pour into mushrooms; heat until soup thickens.
Remove from heat. Serve with a dollop of sour cream for each serving and a sprig of parsley to garnish.

title: no name
directions: Cut sausage into bite-size pieces and brown in large boiler (sausage will cut easily if frozen).
Drain.
Cut green peppers, red peppers and onions into slices.
Add to sausage and simmer. Add crushed tomatoes; let simmer until all vegetables are cooked. Serve over white rice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry balls
directions: Mix large Jell-O together with coconut and chopped pecans. Add can of condensed milk.
Let set a couple of hours.
Roll into little balls.
Dip or roll in small package of Jell-O.

title: sour cream-chili bake
directions: In a skillet brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Stir in drained beans, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce, the 1 cup shredded cheese and onion.
Set aside 1 cup of the corn chips; crush remaining chips coarsely.
Stir crushed chips into meat mixture. Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl.
Add mayonnaise.

title: dark moist chocolate cake
directions: Melt together Baker's chocolate and hot water.
Cool and set aside.
Cream together Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add the cooled chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients a little at a time.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared cake pan(s) and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until dark.

title: scripture cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together the next 7 ingredients and add alternately with the milk to the batter.
Stir in honey and fold in the fruits and nuts.
Mix well. Bake in 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans for 1 hour or until done. Cool 30 minutes before removing cakes from pans to rack to finish cooling.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Mix with eggs, vanilla, milk, margarine and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: grape jelly with gelatin(sugar-free)
directions: In a saucepan, soften gelatin in grape juice and lemon juice. Bring to a rolling boil, dissolving gelatin; boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in liquid sweetener.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal; store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/2 pints.

title: company crab
directions: Thaw crabmeat, if frozen; drain.
Remove any shell or cartilage.
Cut artichoke hearts in half.
Place artichokes in a well-greased shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with mushrooms and crabmeat.
Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour and seasonings.
Add cream gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir in sherry.
Pour sauce over crabmeat.
Combine crumbs and cheese.
Sprinkle over sauce.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bunuelos(fried pastry)
directions: Mix dry ingredients and taste for sugar, then add shortening. Add water slowly to form dough.
Make biscuit size balls and roll out to tortilla size.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add oatmeal, nuts and vanilla.
Roll in wax paper. Chill.
Cut into 3/4-inch slices and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together; serve with vegetables.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain and set aside.
In casserole put 1 can tomato soup (no water) on bottom. Peel and slice potatoes.
Layer on top of soup, then Veg-All and hamburger.
Last spread can of tomato soup over hamburger.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion then drain.
Combine soup and sour cream, then carrots.
Mix with squash and onions.
Melt margarine in skillet and coat stuffing mix.
Spread half of the stuffing mix in a 9 x 12 cake pan.
Add vegetable mixture then cheese.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge candy
directions: Boil sugar, milk and margarine for 8 minutes. Put chocolate bits and Marshmallow Creme over this. First stir with spoon.
Then use mixer until chocolate bits are melted and fudge is real smooth.
Add nuts if desired.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool at room temperature. Cut into squares.

title: grape jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Mix and let jell. This makes a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Melt butter in bottom of oblong casserole.
Sprinkle rice over entire bottom of dish (or pan).
Salt and pepper chicken pieces and place over rice.
Mix celery soup and water; pour over chicken. Sprinkle onion soup mix over last mixture and chicken.
Cover tightly and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine sugar and flour; stir in egg and pineapple juice. Cook over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Cool and fold in Cool Whip.

title: cheemato soup
directions: Combine soup, water and tuna.
Heat.
Add Cheez Whiz and pepper.
Mix until well blended.
Serves 4.

title: watermelon jelly
directions: Put watermelon in food processor or in a blender and blend until smooth (about 2 cups of puree).

title: fluffy gingerbread
directions: Sift flour once, measure and add soda, salt and spices and sift 3 times.
Work butter with spoon until creamy.
Add sugar gradually, beating after each addition until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Add 1/4 of flour and blend.
Add molasses and beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour and beat well.
Add boiling water and stir until blended.
Turn into greased 10 x 13-inch pan and bake in moderate 350° oven for 45 minutes.
After cool, may be iced with buttercream frosting, if desired.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cold linguine salad
directions: Mix altogether and refrigerate overnight.

title: marty's favorite(cracker spread)
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Rinse shrimp and drain well.
Add cream cheese, shrimp, lemon juice and onion or beat on low speed. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve on crackers.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix cake mix, nuts, margarine and 1 egg by hand.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar and pour on top.
Bake on 350° approximately 45 minutes until done.

title: coffee cake
directions: Pour batter into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle sugar mixture on top.
With knife, swirl into batter to marbleize.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° until it looks done.

title: swedish farmer cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and German chocolate together.
Cream butter, sugar and Karo together.
Add to flour.
Roll into logs. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice into thin patties.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and bell pepper until meat is browned; drain.
Add salt and soups and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour into 2 pie shells and bake at 350° until shells are brown.
Turn oven off; add cheese to tops of pies and let them stand in the oven until cheese is melted.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Hollow out mushrooms; dip in melted butter.
Place in shallow pan.
Chop up mushroom pieces left and broccoli/cauliflower pieces.
Set aside.
Crumble up a dozen Ritz crackers.
Add basil, pepper, oregano and garlic powder to taste.
Mix well; add chopped vegetables and mix again.
Add rest of melted butter and mix until all is moist.
Stuff mixture into mushroom caps.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove; top with your favorite cheese and continue baking until cheese melts.
Enjoy!

title: great grandma clow's green tomato relish
directions: Grind (food processor) green tomatoes, green pepper, onions and red pepper.
Place in plastic or pottery container with salt and water to cover.
Stir all together; cover and let stand 24 hours.
Next day, drain brine from vegetables and place in large kettle.
Add remaining ingredients.
I find it best to mix spices with sugar before adding to vegetables with the vinegar; mixes better.
When all is well mixed, cook over medium heat slowly, for about 1/2 hour, stirring often.
Mixture will thicken as it cools.
When cooked, fill pint, sterilized, hot jars to within 1/2-inch of top and seal with sterilized lids and rings.

title: lane cake
directions: Cream butter until smooth, add sugar,
beat until light and fluffy then add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients 5 times.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beat until smooth after each addition.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Grease four 9 inch cake pans, line bottom with wax paper and pour in batter.
Bake in preheated oven 20 minutes at 375 degrees.
Remove and let cool 5 minutes and turn out on racks to completely cool.
Spread Lane filling between layers and ice top and sides of cake.

title: christmas wreath
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows in a steer, then put food coloring in until you reach the color green you desire.
Mix cornflakes in.
Next pour onto tinfoil and shape into a wreath. Finally place the red hots on it.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Drain.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Simmer uncovered until thick, about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles until tender.
Drain and rinse.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Chop rhubarb in unbaked pie shell.
Beat eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Bring
to
a
boil; let simmer 20 minutes.
Put in jars while hot.
Seal tight or put wax on top.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Stir in pecans and fruit of choice. Pour into pie shells and chill several hours.
Makes 2 pies. Freezes well.

title: mamie's corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs until thick, add corn.
Combine flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Very slowly, stir in milk and blend in butter. Combine with corn mixture and bake in 325° oven for about 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir mushrooms and onions in margarine until onion is soft.
Remove from skillet.
In same skillet, brown meat lightly on both sides.
Set aside 1/3 cup bouillon; stir remaining bouillon, ketchup, garlic and salt in skillet.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes.
Blend reserved 1/3 cup bouillon and flour; stir into skillet.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in sour cream; heat through. Serve over cooked egg noodles.

title: savory stuffing balls
directions: Melt butter in pan over medium heat.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add next six ingredients and cook about 5 minutes.
Put bread into large bowl and toss with the hot mixture.
Beat egg, add to chicken broth and mix into bread cubes.
Shape into 2-inch balls and place on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake uncovered about 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 30 balls.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: maria's special
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in a buttered pie plate for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma hosek's zucchini bread(2 loaves)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs; add vanilla, oil and sugar. Stir in zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients and mix together with creamed flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Turn oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour.

title: no eggs homemade ice cream (chocolate)
directions: Mix pudding to directions on box. Mix in rest of ingredients. Pour in freezer and freeze. Let set for 15 minutes and serve.

title: butterscotch pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter until smooth.
Beat in sugars, eggs and vanilla. Mix until well blended.
Gradually add flour, salt, and baking soda.
When well blended, fold in butterscotch chips and pecans. Make a ball from a rounded teaspoon and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes.
If cookies appear a little soft, wait a few seconds before removing from cookie sheet.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Brown steak in butter.
Add small amount of water.
Simmer until tender.
Add small amount of water to onion and celery. Cook until nearly tender.
Cook noodles until tender, drain, rinse and drain.
Combine meat, onion, celery, noodles, seasoning, soup and water.
More water may be added, if mixture seems too thick as it bakes.
Pour into greased casserole.
Cover with cheese, bread crumbs and butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove lid; bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil the eggplant and onion for 10 to 15 minutes in salted water and drain.
Add margarine.
Now add milk, cheese, baking powder and cracker crumbs.
Place in casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: zero dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients together and blenderize.
Shake well before serving.
May be used as desired.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag, add all ingredients and shake until potatoes are well coated.
Empty potatoes into shallow baking dish.
Bake, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: senior guys '94 surprise strawberry sundae dessert
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press half the crumb mixture on bottom of 9-inch square baking pan.

title: mama's (mabel kerr) brown sour milk cake
directions: Cream together the Crisco shortening and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add sour milk alternately with sifted ingredients into creamed mixture; add vanilla.
Batter will be thick.
Blend in raisins and walnuts.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf or 2 small rounds.
Double the recipe and put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 1 hour.
Frost with butter icing.

title: spinach balls
directions: Chill overnight. Roll into small balls. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or done.

title: margaret marinucci's creamy whipped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into quarters.
In 5-quart saucepot over high heat, heat potatoes, 1 teaspoon salt and enough water to cover to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender; drain well.

title: barbecups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown meat; drain.
Add sauce, onion and sugar and set aside.
Separate dough and place each in ungreased muffin cup, pressing dough up sides to edge of cup. Spoon meat mixture into cups.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until golden. Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven until melted.
Makes 10.

title: georgia salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in pineapple juice; heat to dissolve.
Mix cream cheese, pimientos, celery, salt, pineapple and pecans.
Add Jell-O.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate.
Serves 10.

title: best-ever apple pie
directions: *Butter flavor Crisco recommended.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Blend well in large bowl. Chill before serving.
Tomatoes and onions are optional.

title: pinto beans
directions: Soak for 3 hours.
Simmer for 4 hours.

title: pineapple noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles; drain well.
Mix all ingredients well by hand. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: southern black-eyed peas
directions: Combine peas and water in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
In a nonstick skillet, spray with vegetable spray.
Saute onion in pan until soft; add bouillon granules, savory and red pepper flakes and stir to mix.
Add this mixture to beans.
Cover and let simmer 50 minutes or until tender.

title: grilled chicken kabobs
directions: In large plastic zipper seal bag, place chicken pieces and pour marinade over top.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Chop peppers into 1 inch chunks.
On bamboo sticks or skewers, alternate ingredients.
Grill over medium heat for approximately 15 minutes or until done.

title: light and easy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Combine with cooked rice, the celery, onions, margarine, salt, pepper, parsley and carrots and mix.
Place into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken breast.

title: quickie chicken pie
directions: Put meat in bottom of shallow casserole dish (7 x 11-inches). Pour margarine over chicken. Place boiled eggs over chicken and margarine. Mix flour, baking powder and milk. Pour over eggs. Mix soup and chicken broth. Bring to boil and pour over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade soda
directions: Snacking on sugar-rich foods contributes to the decay of healthy teeth.
The "right kinds" of snacks are more nutritious and less costly.
The following are recipe suggestions for lunches, special treats and celebrations.
Help keep your child happy and healthy.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix water and Jell-O.
Add sugar, orange juice, nuts, pineapple and cranberries.
Place in refrigerator for at least 3 hours or until set before serving.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough milk to cream well.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine flour and salt; roll meat in mixture.
Put oil in pot; heat.
Add stew meat and brown slowly.
Add water, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cover tightly and simmer for 1 1/4 hours.
Cut vegetables in quarters.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add vegetables and celery to the stew; cover and simmer an additional hour.

title: double apple salad
directions: In a bowl, toss apples with lemon juice. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Cover and chill for at least 1 hour. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: uncooked covered candy
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients with melted oleo.
Set in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Roll into small balls.
Set back in refrigerator.
Melt paraffin in double boiler with chocolate chips.
Take toothpick and dip small balls in mix.
Place on wax paper.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soup and milk; add Veg-All and chicken.
Stir well.
Pour mixture into one pie crust.
Soften the other pie crust with a little water and place on top of the mixture.
Vent top crust and bake 30 to 45 minutes, until bubbly and golden brown.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and beat.
Add sweet potatoes, Pet milk and salt.
Pour into pie crusts and bake at 350° until firm and brown.

title: me ma's corn pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch dish at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until pudding sets.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook meat with garlic until no longer pink; drain.
Add beans, pepper, tomato sauce, taco sauce and oregano; simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon 1 1/2 cups meat mixture in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer tortillas over sauce (can cut tortillas to fit pan); top with half of remaining meat mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Cover with remaining tortillas and meat mixture.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 20 minutes.
Uncover; top with remaining cheese.
Continue baking until bubbly and cheese is melted.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Top with sour cream if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: two minute fudge
directions: Grease a dish for the fudge.
Chop nuts if desired.
Do these before you put ingredients into microwave as you only have 2 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients in large glass or plastic bowl.
Add milk and vanilla, stir just enough to distribute.
Cut margarine in chunks and drop evenly on top of mixture.
Put in microwave on high 2 minutes 15 seconds.
Stir like mad when it comes out and add chopped nuts if desired.
Pour into previously greased dish and cool or refrigerate.
It's easier to cut into squares before completely cooled.
Enjoy!

title: helen's corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill several hours or overnight.

title: mexican rice meal
directions: Brown rice, onion and chicken with olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add 1 2/3 cups water, kidney beans, olives, peas and corn.
At the simmering point, add tomato sauce and spices.
Stir well and simmer again to almost a boil.
Cover pan and reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand for 15 to 20 minutes more.
Do not open lid until ready to serve or rice will be sticky.
Garnish with grated cheese, sour cream and salsa.
Serve with hot tortillas.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind together cranberries and orange. Dissolve jello in boiling water. Mix cranberries, orange, jello, and sweeten to taste as the cranberries are very tart. Pour in mold and let set. You may add pecans & marshmallows if you like.

title: skillet supper
directions: Brown ground
beef
with celery in medium-sized skillet; drain off
fat.
Stir
in remaining ingredients except noodles, bring to boil.
Sprinkle noodles over mixture; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until noodles are done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and place in pie shell.
Bake in hot oven at 400° about 15 minutes and then reduce to 340° for another 20 minutes.

title: tuna spread
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Drain tuna.
Mix all ingredients until blended and fluffy.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: kim's country cookies
directions: Beat oil, molasses, sugar and egg together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.
Roll into 1-inch balls and dip in granulated sugar.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff 2
directions: Cut meat in thin strips; dip in flour and spices and brown well in oil.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Add rest of ingredients and balance of flour.
Cover; cook slowly until slightly thick and add sour cream at last minute.
Do not overcook.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend first three ingredients and pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sift together the next three ingredients.

title: meat and potato country pie
directions: In a greased baking dish, put a thin layer of mashed potatoes. Salt and pepper; add small pieces of margarine.
Next, place layer of meat, then layer of sliced onion.
Next, use remaining potatoes and bake in moderate oven until hot and lightly browned.

title: refrigerator cheese cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter and sugar and blend well.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 2/3 of crumbs. Reserve rest of crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Cream the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, lemon juice and vanilla until smooth.
Beat the evaporated milk in a large bowl (milk and bowl should be well chilled), until stiff peaks form.
Fold in cream cheese mixture and jello and blend well.
Pour into crumb lined pan and sprinkle remaining crumbs on the top.
Cover with foil and chill at least 8 hours before serving.

title: microwave taco casserole
directions: Melt oleo in 2-quart casserole dish in microwave.
Add hamburger and cook until all pink has disappeared, stirring through cooking time, about 5 minutes.
Add taco seasoning, tomato sauce and water.
Cook for 4 minutes more, stirring well.
Lightly stir in coarsely broken chips.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Garnish with tomato (optional).
Liberally sprinkle with cheese on top. Cook until cheese is melted.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, water and oil together.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight.

title: dr. pepper chili
directions: Place meat in a large sauce pan, cook.
Add onions, garlic and cook, stirring with fork to break up meat.
Cook until light brown.
Add salt, tomatoes or paste, Dr. Pepper, and some water. Simmer until meat is tender.

title: cottage cheese pie(this recipe is a frey family favorite)
directions: Beat all ingredients together until well blended.
Bake in pie crust at 350° until the filling is firm.
(Use top and bottom crust; sprinkle sugar over top crust.)

title: salmon loaf
directions: Add lemon juice to salmon; set aside.
In saucepan, melt butter, then blend in flour, salt and milk.
Cook to a smooth sauce.
Add onion, celery, eggs, bread crumbs, peas and salmon. Bake at 350° in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan for 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator all-bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over Nabisco 100% All-Bran.
Cream Crisco, white sugar, well beaten eggs, buttermilk and Kellogg's All-Bran. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; stir well.
Fold in soaked bran.
Bake in greased tins for 15 to 18 minutes at 400°.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix apples with other ingredients.
Add 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice to keep fruit from darkening.
Place in unbaked crust.
Add top crust and bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: applesauce fruit nut cake
directions: Place all ingredients in pan of your choice.
Bake at about 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: fannie's oatmeal cake
directions: Mix and let stand 20 minutes, oats and boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: baked raspberry vanilla pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly butter a 9-inch pie plate or a 1-quart shallow baking dish.
Spread the raspberries and their juice evenly on bottom of pie plate.
Make the batter.
In blender, mix eggs, milk, cream, flour, 1/4 cup of sugar and vanilla; blend well.
Pour batter over fruit.
Sprinkle with extra tablespoon of sugar.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until pudding is set and golden around edges.

title: oatmeal polka dots
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Add mace and salt to flour.
Stir to blend.
Add blended dry ingredients, rolled oats and nuts to creamed mixture.
Mix well; let stand for 10 minutes.
Shape dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press down in center with finger.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Press down in center again.
Return to oven and bake 5 to 7 minutes more.
Melt chocolate bits in top of double boiler.
Fill center with 1/4 teaspoon of melted chocolate.

title: fudge squares
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spread mixture into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: georgia cake
directions: Place margarine, oil and water in small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Meanwhile, place remaining ingredients in mixing bowl. Pour hot mixture over this.
Beat well; mixture will be thin! Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and then mix other ingredients.

title: raspberry oatmeal bars
directions: Combine cake mix and oatmeal.
Stir in melted margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Put about 3 cups of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan and press firmly.
Combine jam and water and spoon over crumb mixture; spread evenly.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture; make top even by patting firmly.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool before cutting into bars.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Serve over noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco pie
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook beef and onion in skillet over medium low heat, stirring to crumble until brown.
Drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in pie plate; sprinkle with chiles.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth (15 seconds in blender or 1 minute with hand mixer).
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes more or until knife inserted to center somes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream (optional), tomatoes, shredded lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: noni's blueberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine; add sugar until fluffy.
Add egg; beat well.
Add flour, alternating with milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Coat blueberries with 4 teaspoons of flour; fold into batter.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl. Mix well. Spread thinly on flour tortillas. Roll as for jellyrolls. Chill thoroughly. Cut into 1-inch pieces.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a buttered and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot bars
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
In separate bowl, combine flour and baking powder, gradually add to butter mixture.
Add coconut, walnuts and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Shred lettuce in salad bowl.
Layer celery, eggs, peppers, onions and bacon on top of lettuce.
Mix mayonnaise with sugar. Spread this over top of salad.
Sprinkle cheese over this.

title: ham and swiss cheese biscuits
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender, add other ingredients, except ham and Swiss cheese.

title: southern sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage in a large saucepan; drain partially.
Crumble sausage; return to pan.
Add milk to flour; beat with a whisk until flour dissolves.
Add to sausage.
Add red pepper flakes; cook over medium heat until thickened, approximately 1/2 hour, stirring often.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over homemade biscuits.

title: pat jenneskens' artichoke and mushroom chicken
directions: Put flour in a plastic bag.
Add chicken and shake to coat thoroughly.
Heat oil in a frypan over medium heat.
Add chicken and saute until golden.
Remove to a warm platter and keep warm. Pour off any oil left in pan.
Add butter and melt over medium heat.
Add garlic, artichoke hearts and mushrooms.
Saute for 5 minutes.

title: pineapple diet dessert
directions: Put 2 tablespoons of juice in blender.
Sprinkle in the gelatin and blend.
Boil 6 tablespoons juice.
Add sweetener and the vanilla.
Pour into blender; add cheese.
Blend.
Arrange pineapple slices in individual bowls.
Pour blended ingredients over, dividing evenly among the 8 containers.
Refrigerate until set.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake about 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 1 hour.
Cool and cut chicken up in pieces.
Mix chicken, cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soup, jalapeno peppers, onions, salt and pepper.
Put 1 layer of mixture and 1 layer of cheese.
Repeat procedure until mixture is gone. Cover with cheese.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry pie
directions: Mix strawberries, milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crusts.
Freeze.

title: roxy's taco salad
directions: Break up
lettuce,
drain beans, chop olives, tomatoes, green peppers and
green onions.
Brown burger and season with 1/4
to 1/2 teaspoon chili powder, 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon cumin, salt and pepper.
Drain meat.

title: meat ball casserole
directions: Blend and mix well together ground beef, onion, green pepper, egg, salt and pepper.
Add milk to mushroom soup and stir.
Then add soup mixture to meat mixture and mix well.
Form into balls; dip in flour and brown in skillet.
Place in greased casserole. Combine chili sauce with remaining soup mixture.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: On crust, slice bananas thin.
Beat milk and lemon juice; pour over bananas.
Put drained pineapple on next layer.
Cover all with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts, coconut and cherries.
Chill well.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter and beaten egg.
Add milk.
Divide dough in half.
Pat first half in greased cake pan.
Brush with melted butter.
Place second layer on top.
Sprinkle with a little sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with berries and whipped cream.

title: bronze medal brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients until mixed well. Pour into greased pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Test with toothpick. Remove from pan before they are cool.

title: taco salad for one(only 200 calories)
directions: Layer ingredients in any order.
Sprinkle with taco seasoning if you like.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in microwave.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: toasted butter pecans
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, place pecan halves and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Cut butter into 4 pieces and arrange evenly over top.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes; stir and turn. Microwave on High for an additional 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Chop
raisins
coarsely,
if desired. Resift flour with baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Add caraway seed. Cut
in shortening until in fine pieces.
Make well in center. Pour in buttermilk and add raisins.
Mix lightly to moderately soft dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead gently a few strokes. Shape into round ball.
Put into greased 8 or 9-inch layer
cake pan.
Cut
loaf crosswise into quarters about 2/3 way
through dough
with
sharp knife.
Brush top with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crispy fried okra
directions: Slice okra.
In large skillet, cover bottom with oil.
Heat until hot.
In bag, place sugar, flour and okra.
Shake until coated.
Drop in pan; cook and flip until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Drain peas and mix with pimento, soup, salt and cheese.
Put in a baking dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers; then place pats of margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Pour pineapple juice in punch bowl.
Add lime sherbet and add the ginger ale.

title: cheese sauce
directions: To increase sauce, add 1 c. shredded sharp Cheddar cheese, grated.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Press graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° until cheese is set and very lightly golden. Don't overbake.
Cool and top with 1 can cherry pie filling. Cover that with 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes in skin, peel and mash.
Combine sugar, milk and eggs.
Add to potatoes.
Add more milk, if needed, to make mixture pourable.
Add nutmeg and vanilla to potatoes and pour into baked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Test for doneness, when straw inserted comes out clean.

title: j.o.y. circle lasagna
directions: Brown beef. Add all other ingredients; mix well. Grease 9 x 13 pan. Layer sauce and noodles, beginning with sauce. Put in refrigerator overnight. Heat at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours. Fork will go into noodles easily.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, rub over chicken halves.
Place chicken, skin side up, in a pan.
Pour over any extra soy mixture. Baked at 400° until done.
Skin and bone chicken and cut into thin strips.
Spread sesame seed in a pan over low heat, shaking until seed turns golden and begins to pop.
In a salad bowl, mix chicken, lettuce, onion, coriander, sesame seed and nuts.
Add dressing and noodles.

title: low country boil
directions: Fill 4 to 5 gallon stock pot 3/4 full of water.
Put in bags of crab boil when water boils.
Add sausage and all vegetables. Cook until vegetables are tender, approximately 45 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 5 additional minutes.
Ladle out into a large serving dish and serve with French bread.

title: almond chiffon pie
directions: Scald milk in boiler over low heat.
Sprinkle gelatine over water.
Separate eggs.
Set aside whites (and cover).
Beat yolks, sugar and salt with fork.
When milk is scalded, pour some into egg mixture, then add egg mixture to rest of milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until thick as custard sauce.
Pour some over gelatine; stir, dissolving gelatine and add gelatine to remaining milk mixture, blending.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Line a baking sheet with waxed paper.
Melt chocolate. Remove from the heat.
Add the noodles
and peanuts and stir and fold until the noodles are well coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto the prepared pan.
Chill for at least 8 hours or until ready to serve.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix butter, cheese and soup in saucepan; heat until cheese has melted.
Add rice and broccoli; mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Add carrots to salted boiling water.
Bring quickly to a boil. Cover; reduce heat.
Cook gently until tender (about 10 minutes). Melt butter in small pan.
Add sugar.
Cook until dissolved. Coat drained carrots well.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple coconut pies
directions: Beat eggs in blender. Slowly add sugar; add oleo and salt, then pineapple and coconut. Pour into pie shells. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook green beans and drain.
Place green beans and chicken in a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine soup and 1/3 cup water; pour over beans and chicken.
Combine stuffing, butter and remaining water; toss lightly.
Place over ingredients in baking dish.
Beat egg whites until stiff enough to form soft peaks.
Fold egg whites into yolks and spoon over casserole.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with French fried onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: gerry's orange dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook the sweet potatoes in water. Drain off the liquid, then mash.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add the yellow cornmeal, then stir.
In a small bowl, combine both types of sugar.
Add the eggs to the sugar mixture and cream until fluffy.

title: overnight pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water.
Drain and cool.
Place lettuce in bottom of 2-quart dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with macaroni.
Layer egg slices with salt.
Layer ham strips, peas and cheese.
Combine salad dressing, sour cream, onion, mustard, hot sauce and spread over top of salad, sealing to edge of dish. Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or overnight.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Toss before serving.

title: texas triple dip
directions: Layer equal amounts of guacamole, dairy sour cream and picante sauce in a clear glass bowl.
Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.
Serves 8 to 12 people.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift flour and spices together and add to mixture.
Add food coloring and plums.
Mix well and add nuts.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Cool.
Glaze with 1 cup powdered sugar thinned with lemon juice to suit taste.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Flour each piece of chicken; dip into beaten eggs and roll in bread crumbs. Deep-fry until golden brown. Serve with honey mustard or honey or your favorite dipping sauce.

title: one rise mixer rolls
directions: Grease 14 medium muffin cups.
In large mixer bowl, dissolve yeast in hot water.
Add 1 1/3 cups of the flour and the remaining ingredients.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes on high speed or 300 strokes by hand, scraping bowl constantly.
Stir in remaining flour thoroughly.

title: sugar-free popsicles
directions: Mix hot water and Jell-O until dissolved.
Add Kool-Aid and cold water. Pour into paper cups.
Makes 18 to 24 popsicles.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, peanut butter and butter. Mix with nuts, dates and coconut. When well mixed, roll into small balls with your hands. Refrigerate while melting almond bark over low heat. When melted, with 2 teaspoons dip the balls into the hot bark to coat, then place on wax paper. Place in refrigerator until hard on outside.

title: banana split pie
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Pour filling into a graham cracker crust.
Cover with slices of banana (quarters).
Pour 1 large can of drained, crushed pineapple over.
Spread one large bowl of Cool Whip.
Add pecans and cherries on top.
Makes 2 pies.

title: raisin bars
directions: Cook raisins in water.
Melt butter in 1 cup of hot raisin juice (add a little water to juice if not 1 cup).
Add raisins. In another bowl sift sugar, flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to raisin mixture.
Add nuts.
Batter will be thin. Pour in large flat pan (jelly roll pan) that has been greased and floured.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Ice with powdered sugar, coffee, maple extract and butter.
Cut into bars.

title: mini salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; flake with a fork.
Add 3 eggs, garlic, 1/2 cup breadcrumbs, celery, onion and thyme.
Mix well.
Form into 12 small patties.
Beat remaining egg.
Brush egg on both sides of each patty.
Coat with breadcrumbs.
Refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Fry patties in hot oil until golden.

title: chicken, pot roasted
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Arrange chicken, potatoes, onions and carrots in baking dish. Pour lemon juice over vegetables. Sprinkle on garlic, oregano, thyme and pepper. Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender. Turn veggies and chicken. Occasionally
baste with pan juices. When ready, place on serving dish sprinkled with parsley.

title: jonathan's rice casserole and broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot or bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until broccoli is tender and cheese is melted.

title: "ev's" cara mia rice
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Mix artichokes, including liquid, mayonnaise, olives and bell pepper.
Pour into rice mixture; stir well.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve.
Makes approximately 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender in small amount of water. Remove from heat; add salt, pepper and butter.
Mix cracker crumbs, egg, milk and 1/2 of cheese.
Then add to squash.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, depending on how hot your squash is.

title: country butter
directions: A touch of country with a taste like home churned butter. Leave margarine at room temperature to soften for a couple of hours.
Beat with a blender or beater all ingredients.
Fold into bowl and cover.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Can be frozen for several months.
To save time and money, freeze several at a time.
The cheapest stick margarine may be used or if need be, corn oil or a reasonable facsimile for cholesterol problems.

title: june's blueberry pie
directions: Mix 1 pint blueberries, flour, butter, salt and lemon juice together in heavy saucepan.
Add sugars.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Do not add liquid.
Cook until mix thickens, about 5 minutes.
Cool; add remaining blueberries.
Fill pie shell with blueberry mixture and chill.
When ready to serve, top with sweetened whipped cream.

title: low-fat carrot soup
directions: Peel and dice carrots and potatoes.
Add them to 4 cups water. Cook until tender.
Blend with water.
Pour back into pot, add bouillon and garlic.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate rum mousse pie
directions: In small cup, sprinkle gelatin over cold water; let stand 1 minute to soften.
Add boiling water; stir until gelatin is completely dissolved and mixture is clear.
Cool slightly, about 5 minutes.

title: easy pizza dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: pappy and grandma baer's mincemeat
directions: Cook meat, mashing into fine pieces.
Add other ingredients. Cook/simmer several hours.
Add thickening (cornstarch or cleargel, if necessary), if you've added more cider than necessary.
Add anything else from refrigerator, such as leftover fruit, cranberry salad, etc.
Freeze leftovers for pie making all winter.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Beat brown sugar and oleo until fluffy.
Stir in baking mix and walnuts until mixture is crumbly; reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining mixture in pan.
Bake 12 minutes.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix
all ingredients and then form into balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: lemon cream
directions: Put jello in dish.
Put pineapple in strainer; pour boiling water over it onto jello.
Whip cream; combine with egg white, beaten with sugar.
After jello has hardened a bit, stir in cream and egg white mixture.

title: apple butter
directions: You will need a heavy kettle or pot.

title: honey cookies
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Melt margarine and cool. Add 1 cup sugar, beat well.
Add egg; beat.
Add honey.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Roll into a ball about the size of a small hickory nut. Mix last 3 ingredients together and roll balls into mixture.
Bake at 350° about 8 - 10 minutes.
They will flatten as they bake.

title: marinated grilled chicken
directions: Blend oil, lemon juice, onion and garlic until fairly smooth. Add spices.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator or at room temperature for 2 hours.
Turn twice while marinating.
Grill over medium coals until done (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Serves 4.

title: no bake cake
directions: Crumble angel food cake; spread evenly in bottom of a large, oblong pan.
Pour pineapple over cake.
Heat milk and marshmallows until marshmallows melt.
Pour over cake and pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over top and chill.

title: hot milk pound cake
directions: You can add lemon and coconut flavoring, if you like.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese and parsley with salt and pepper to taste.
Melt butter and garlic.
Dip chicken breasts in butter. Then in crumb mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.

title: scandinavian apple cake
directions: Peel, core and chop apples; combine apples, sugar, nuts and butter in a large bowl.
Stir in eggs; add vanilla.
Sift together all dry ingredients and add to apple mixture, stirring until blended.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (8-inch) square cake pans.
Divide batter between pans and bake 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.
Can also be baked in a 9 x 13-inch dish; bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peach frozen yogurt
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over milk in a saucepan; let stand 1 minute. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves. Remove from heat and add sugar and salt, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Stir in yogurt, vanilla and pureed peaches.
Cover and chill.
Pour yogurt mixture into freezer can of a 4-quart hand-turned or electric freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Scoop yogurt into individual dishes. Serve immediately.
Yields 7 1/2 cups (about 82 calories per 1/2-cup serving).

title: microwave banana pudding
directions: Microwave
sugar,
cornstarch,	3 cups milk and salt on High; stirring
every
3 minutes, until it starts to thicken. Add beaten egg yolks, butter, vanilla and 1 cup milk.	Continue to microwave on High, stirring every 3 minutes, for approximately 9 to 12 minutes.
Remove from microwave and add sliced bananas
and vanilla
wafers.
Save
some
vanilla wafers and place on top of mixture.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Dissolve soda in hot water; mix all together with mixer.
Drop batter by small spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: lady bird's lima beans
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine.
Sprinkle in flour.
Add slowly and cook until thickened the milk.
Blend cheese, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Stir beans in gently.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, cornstarch, syrup and vanilla until thick. Remove form heat and add jello.
Place strawberries in cooked pie shells.
Pour jello mixture over strawberries.
Refrigerate until cool. Serve with Cool Whip topping.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1-quart casserole, stir soup and soy sauce until smooth. Mix in 1/2 can onions, beans and pepper.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes more. Makes 6 servings.

title: old fashioned shortbread cookie
directions: Cream butter; gradually add powdered sugar and cornstarch, beating at medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy. Stir in flour.
Firmly press dough in lightly greased and floured 9-inch cookie mold.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Invert cookie from pan and let cool on rack.

title: date loaf
directions: Cook sugar and milk until it forms soft ball.
Stir in dates and cook until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Remove from fire; stir in nuts and coconut.
Roll out on damp cloth.
Let cool, then slice.

title: melting moments
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch and sugar in a bowl.
Blend in margarine to form dough.
Cover and chill until dough is firm enough to handle. Shape into small balls about 3/4-inch thick.
Roll in coconut and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork. Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 3 dozen.

title: true to texas chili
directions: Brown onion, garlic and beef together in 6-quart Dutch oven. Add sauce and spices.
Bring to boil.
Add beans.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: collard greens
directions: Cut up collards; wash with cold water several times.
Then place in 5-quart pot and cook on high for a few minutes.
Then turn heat down to medium-high.
Fry fatback in skillet.
Use fatback drippings to season collards.
Stir often to make sure collards don't stick.

title: raisin-nut muffins
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg and milk; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Coat paper muffin pan liners with cooking spray.
Spoon batter into liners, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Yields 6 muffins.

title: reuben dip
directions: Heat all together and dip rye crackers in it.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased and floured large jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.
Frost.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
