directions: *I measured while watching Mother make these; I use about 2 1/2 cups.

title: steak soup
directions: Make roux from oleo and flour.
Slowly add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: mandarin cream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges with electric mixer until well blended.
Bake in two 9-inch round cake pans (greased) for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.
Cool on wire racks.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: beef and cheese enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion; drain and add cumin and garlic powder.
In a separate 1-quart pan combine cheese, milk, soup and green chilies and cook on medium heat until melted and smooth.
Pour about 1 cup of cheese sauce into a 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Place about 3 tablespoons of meat in tortillas and roll up.
Place seam down in dish.
Pour remaining sauce over rolled tortillas.
Heat in 350° oven until sauce is bubbling. Sprinkle top with shredded cheese.
Makes about 7 tortillas.

title: one minute cookies-chocolate or peanut butter
directions: Bring sugar, oleo, milk and chocolate chips or cocoa to a full boil in pan and boil 1 minute.
Add oats and stir.
Drop on wax paper.
Can use 2 1/2 cups oats and 1/2 cup coconut.
Can use peanut butter chips for peanut butter cookies.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Slice kielbasa in 1/2 inch thick slices.
Combine in crock-pot with jelly and chili sauce.
Simmer on low 3 to 4 hours or until warm.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In skillet, brown the hamburger and onion.
Transfer to saucepan after draining meat.
Add water and tomatoes.
Heat to boiling.
Add carrots and rice.
Cook until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: german skillet dinner
directions: Brown meat; drain and turn on paper towel.
Drain fat well. Rinse sauerkraut and drain.
Add all ingredients together in skillet and mix well.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes over low heat or put in casserole, cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix the 2 cans of corn (undrained) with all of the remaining ingredients, making sure sour cream and margarine are mixed in well.
Pour into 7 x 11-inch casserole.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until brown and the center is firm.

title: sweet and spicy chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients, except wings, in a bowl.
Toss wings in marinade.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Drain and reserve marinade. Broil wings on rack in broiler for 5 minutes on each side, brushing with reserved marinade.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Sift together the last 5 ingredients; set aside.

title: doughnut balls
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until brown; drain on paper towel.
While warm, roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture or powdered sugar.

title: jean's carrot cake
directions: Blend oil, eggs and honey in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add dry ingredients and beat well.
Add vanilla, carrots, raisins and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in oiled and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with softened cream cheese, if desired.

title: california chicken salad
directions: Melt 1 stick butter; let cool. Gently stir butter and 2 cups mayonnaise with minced parsley. Add curry powder, salt, marjoram and white pepper. Mix cooked chicken with grapes and almonds. Mix all together and serve on croissants.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a small saucepan, cook cream 8 to 10 minutes over medium heat until volume is reduced by half. In a large saucepot over medium heat, cook bacon until cooked, but not crispy.
Add celery to pot; cook 5 minutes until softened.
Stir in chicken broth, bottled clam juice and reserved clam juice; bring to a simmer.
In a blender, puree cooked cauliflower, cream and 1 cup of soup until very smooth. Return to saucepot. Stir in clams.
Bring soup to a simmer; cook 5 minutes.
Season with Tabasco and Worcestershire sauces.
Swirl in butter until incorporated.
Serve hot.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add corn, tomato sauce, salsa and taco seasoning mix.
Simmer, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes.
In a separate bowl, combine cottage or Ricotta cheese, eggs and oregano.
Line bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch dish with 5 tortillas, overlapping edges.
Top with half of meat mixture. Spoon cheese mixture over meat.
Arrange 5 tortillas over cheese mixture.
Spread remaining meat mixture over all and top with shredded cheese.

title: cream cheese peach pie
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and spread in a 9-inch pie pan. Drain and pour the peaches over this dough.

title: peach or berry cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in long pan. Mix first 4 ingredients to make batter, then pour in pan. Put peaches on top of batter, (don't pour them in), Use large spoon, have plenty of juice.
Bake in 400° oven approx 40 min. (may also add a little almond or vanilla flavoring)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
May sprinkle top with crushed potato chips or stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Freezes well for cooking layer.
I double or triple the recipe and freeze in different sized casseroles.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Grease wax paper with butter and set aside.
Cut butter or margarine into 1/2 inch pieces.
Combine sugar and next 5 ingredients in large heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat stirring gently, until butter melts.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture reaches ball stage on candy thermometer reads 238° (about 15 minutes).
Remove from heat, stir in pecans and flavorings.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onions.
Drain fat.
Stir in Mexican-style beans, tomato sauce, green chilies and taco seasoning.
Layer half the tortillas on bottom of an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Spread half the meat mixture over and sprinkle with half the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage and mozzarella roll
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain off grease.
Roll out bread dough to the size of a cookie sheet.
Spread sausage mixture on dough.
Sprinkle cheese on top of sausage.
Roll as you would a jelly roll.
Use toothpicks to hold roll together.
Brush top with egg yolk.
Sprinkle sesame seed over roll.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit thoroughly.
Mix in other ingredients and chill. Keeps well in refrigerator for several days.
Serves 6.

title: creamy mints
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Press into candy mold and unmold at once.
If candy sticks, add more powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Mix with fork until mixture resembles coarse meal. Spread half of the mixture in pie shell. Set remaining mixture aside.

title: sauerkraut dumplings
directions: Mix until thick and sticky.
Drop into boiling water by small teapsoonfuls.
Cook about 3 minutes.
Add to sauerkraut and cook with sauerkraut until done.

title: fresh fruit compote
directions: Combine ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Chop 6 maraschino cherries and add them and three drops red food coloring to sauce.
Refrigerate in covered container.
Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Add flour.
Use a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: fire cracker corn salad(makes 5 servings)
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together vegetable juice, vinegar, parsley and garlic.
Add rice, chilies, corn and pimiento.
Mix well.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or until ready to serve.

title: ham stew
directions: Cook bacon and crumble.
Add ham, Veg-All and tomato soup. Heat and serve over egg noodles.
Add grated cheese if you like.

title: butter-herb baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except butter. Melt butter.
Dip fish in butter and then in crumb mixture. Arrange fish fillets in baking pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish is tender.

title: italian chicken
directions: Salt chicken breasts and place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour or until tender.
Remove foil.
Sprinkle cheese over chicken and return to oven until cheese is melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: grandma metcalf's graham bread
directions: Sift white flour.
Add sugar and graham flour.
Add molasses and buttermilk with soda dissolved in it.
Mix well.
Bake at 300° for at least 3/4 hour.
Test with toothpick to make sure middle is done.
Good source of fiber.
Delicious with peanut butter.

title: "cimarron red"(the oklahoma chili company)
directions: Sear meat in large stock pot or Dutch oven.
When lightly brown, add onions, garlic powder and tomatoes (with juice). Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes to an hour or so, stirring occasionally.
Add chili powder (use the freshest you can find), oregano, pepper sauce, salt and m.s.g.
Cover and simmer for one hour, stirring occasionally.
Add cayenne pepper.
Stir a little beer into the masa until it forms a thin paste and add to chili while stirring.
Add the remaining beer and simmer for an additional 30 minutes or so, stirring occasionally, uncovered if you want the chili thicker or covered if it's thick enough.
Serve with any or all of the following: beans, grated cheese, sour cream, chopped onion, sweet relish, corn bread, etc.
The chili will freeze well and is even better when reheated.

title: chicken delight
directions: Spray Pyrex dish with oil.
Combine chicken, parsley, salt and pepper and half the cheese.
Lay out each roll in the Pyrex dish.
Put 1/4 of mixture in each roll.
Wrap up like a diaper. Mix soup with 1 can milk or water.
Pour over each roll until gone.
Top each with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: german pizza
directions: In a 12-inch stove top or electric skillet, over medium heat, brown beef with onions, green pepper, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper. Remove mixture from skillet and drain fat.

title: monkey bread
directions: Make little balls with bread.
Roll each ball in sugar and cinnamon.
Place pecans
in Bundt pan with rolls on top.
Let raise.

title: maple butter
directions: Put all ingredients except butter into a pot and bring to a boil.
Boil 20 to 30 minutes at medium-high heat.
Stir often. Cool for about 20 minutes.
Add butter and stir until the consistency of cream.

title: "just like" mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour and oatmeal (put a small amount in blender after measuring and blend until it turns to powder; return to bowl), salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Combine with butter mixture.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make golf-ball size cookies, placing them 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: toasted butter pecan cheese round
directions: Combine cream cheese and toasted pecans.
Mix well and form into round disk about 1 inch thick.
Just before serving, pour glaze over top and around plate.
Serve with round butter-type crackers.

title: terrence's favorite pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: honey fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cream and chocolate for 5 minutes.
Add honey and cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water; 236°.
Remove from heat and allow to cool to 120°.
Beat until it loses its shiny look.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cut in 1 inch squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: veal roman style
directions: About 1 hour before serving, do this:

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise and remove seeds.
Peel and dice. Cook sausage and onion; drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven or until zucchini is tender.

title: brown betty
directions: Grease a pudding dish; put in a layer of nice cooking apples (sliced), then a layer of bread crumbs.
Put small bits of butter over this and sprinkle with sugar.
For 3 apples, use 1 cup bread crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar and butter the size of an egg.
Have a layer of bread crumbs for the top; bake or steam.

title: chocolate turtle cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine wafer crumbs and margarine. Press into bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
In 1-quart heavy saucepan, melt caramels with milk over low heat, stirring frequently, until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Top with pecans.
Combine cream cheese, granulated sugar and vanilla, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in chocolate; pour over pecans.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan.
Cool before removing rim of pan.
Chill.

title: spunky beef jerky
directions: Mix marinade (all ingredients except meat) and let stand overnight.
Add beef (or deer) and let stand in refrigerator for 24 to 48 hours.
Drain meat well, squeezing by hand.
Lay on cookie sheets and place in oven at 150° to 175°.
After about 4 hours, drain excess moisture.
Turn and dry to desired dryness. If desired, sprinkle with coarse ground pepper after draining moisture.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Steam vegetables just until tender.
Combine all ingredients except 1/2 of the cheese and 1 cup of onions.
Pour into a shallow 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, about 15 minutes or until heated through.
Top with cheese and remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden, but not burnt. Serves 6.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour in a greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: sparkling orange eggnog
directions: In large bowl, measure 3 cups of the orange juice, eggs, sugar, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and lemon juice.
Blend with mixer.
Stir in remaining orange juice; cover and refrigerate. Before serving, pour eggnog mixture into large punch bowl, spoon in ice cream and add ginger ale.
Blend with mixer.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: twinkies cake
directions: Split Twinkies lengthwise.
Place cream side up in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Slice
bananas
and
lay
over
Twinkies.
Mix pudding; spread.
Spread on pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip. Put nuts and cherries on top.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: granola
directions: Mix together the oil and honey in large bowl. Add the oats, coconut, nuts and seeds. Mix well and place in 2 large Pyrex dishes. Sprinkle each dish with 1/2 cup brown sugar. Bake at 200° to 225° for 1 to 2 hours, stirring about every 15 minutes. Cook until a golden brown or desired crunchiness. Cool and store in airtight containers.

title: reese's candy
directions: Melt margarine or butter; stir in peanut butter until mixed and smooth.
Stir in crumbs.
Stir in powdered sugar with a wooden spoon or hands until thoroughly mixed.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips; spread over top of candy.
When the chocolate is hard, cut into squares.
Do not refrigerate.
Store in a tightly covered container.

title: dirt cake
directions: Pulverize cookies in blender.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip, butter and sugar.
In another bowl, mix puddings, milk and vanilla, then mix the two mixtures together.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening and margarine into dry ingredients with pastry blender.
Add water reserving a little in case it's not needed (dough should not be so sticky that it sticks all over your hands). Mix good with your hands.
Roll out on pastry cloth that has been lightly floured.
Cut in circle larger than your pie pan and place in pan.
Prick crust all over with fork.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes if a cooked crust is needed.

title: "banana split flip"
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar and margarine. Spread in pan and bake at 375° for 7 minutes. Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar. Pour over crust. Layer sliced bananas and pineapple. Spread Cool Whip over these and sprinkle pecans, cherries and slivered Hershey bar on top. Refrigerate.

title: jan's strawberry delight
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix jello in bowl; add frozen strawberries and stir until strawberries are thawed.
Pour over cake.
Mix vanilla pudding; pour over cake.
Mix 1 envelope of Dream Whip as directed and pour over cake.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed, only substitute pineapple for water.
Stir in coconut and rum flavoring into batter.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Cut each hot dog into 4 pieces.
Wrap a small piece of cut bacon around hot dog piece and secure with toothpick.
Put all bacon wrapped hot dogs into a crock-pot.
Pour brown sugar over hot dogs and cook on high 3 to 4 hours until bacon is fully cooked. Stir 1 to 2 times during cooking.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon in individual salad molds and place in freezer for 12 hours.
Serve frozen. This makes 10 servings.
Chunk pineapple or other fruit can be used instead of fruit cocktail if you prefer.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Tear angel food cake into bite size pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat together cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk; fold in Cool Whip. Spread mixture over cake. Mix sliced strawberries and glaze together and spread over the top. Chill.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour over mixed vegetables.
Chill and drain before serving.
Field peas and cornbread are my favorites with this salad.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Brown in olive oil.
Saute onion until golden.
Add mushrooms.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add wine.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add all others including chicken.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Layer potatoes, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers to desired amount.
Pour whipping cream over the potatoes (about 3/4 full).
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Beat egg.
Add sugar, cocoa, melted butter, sifted flour and salt.
Mix well. Grease pan. Cook in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake as directed.
When cool, use 1/2 the cake mix and crumble it in the bottom of the (preferably) punch bowl.

Then sprinkle 2 packets of the hot chocolate mix on top of the cake. Then spread 1 to 2 cans of chocolate pudding over the mix. (Depending on how thick you want it, depends on the amount of pudding to add.
I use 2.)
Then spread 1 container of Cool Whip over the pudding.
Then sprinkle 3 Heath bars (crunched) over the consistency.
Repeat the entire steps in same order for second layer.

title: memama's corn chowder
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch segments and brown to a crisp.
Add onion and saute.
While this is cooking, boil potatoes until soft; drain water, leaving enough to cover an inch above potatoes.
When cooked, add bacon, onion, corn and milk to potatoes and simmer on low for 30 minutes.
Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix well altogether, pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: amish cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, beat 5 minutes with mixer.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop or make small balls of dough.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: nut 'n bolts (nibblers)lubbock, texas
directions: Place first mixture in a large baking pan or roaster.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix melted butter and cracker crumbs in bottom of dish to make crust.
Beat powdered sugar, eggs and sticks of butter in mixing bowl 5 to 6 minutes or until fluffy.
Pour mixture over crust. Slice bananas and cover mixture.
Add pineapple over banana layer. Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Top with cherries and refrigerate before serving.

title: curtis bay rice pudding
directions: Wash rice.
Place in saucepan with 2 cups water and bring to a boil. Cook, uncovered, over low heat until rice has absorbed water and is tender. Remove from heat.
Rinse rice again in colander; drain well.
Return rice to saucepan with milk and condensed milk. Cook over low heat until there is just a thin layer of liquid covering the rice.
Remove from heat.
Add egg, sugar, nutmeg to taste and vanilla. Add a squeeze or two of fresh lemon juice. Sprinkle surface with cinnamon.
Let cool at room temperature, then refrigerate.
If raisins are desired, plump in boiling water for a few minutes, then drain before adding to rice with egg and seasonings.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hanky panks
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add chopped cheese and spices.
Spread on party rye.
Put on cookie sheet and place in freezer for 20 minutes, then pile them up in a plastic bag.
Place in freezer until needed.
Thaw.
Put under broiler for a few minutes until bubbly.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Set oven to 350°.
Mix the flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, baking powder and spices.
In a separate, large bowl, mix pumpkin, eggs, oil and water.
Add flour mixture and stir just until blended.
Stir in dates and nuts (optional).
Bake about 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Can be sprinkled with powdered sugar or frosted.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for 2 round pans, 40 to 45 minutes for 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Goes good with Decorating Icing.

title: sand dabs cookies
directions: Melt margarine and cool.
Mix all together and form in small balls about the size of a walnut.
Place in an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until slightly brown, about 8 to 10 minutes at 325°. Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Sift flour; add baking powder and salt, set aside.
Mix 1 stick margarine and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and syrup alternately to creamed mixture.
Bake in greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch) for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook and stir zucchini and onion in margarine for 10 minutes. Stir in spices.
Combine beaten eggs and cheese.
Stir into zucchini mixture.
Press crescent rolls over bottom and up sides of 12 x 8-inch baking dish to form crust.
Spread crust with 2 teaspoons of mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture into crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: italian eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut lengthwise into 1/8-inch thick slices; sprinkle with salt.
Place eggplant in single layers between pieces of paper towel and let stand for 40 minutes.
Press to remove moisture.
Combine egg, milk and 2 teaspoons oil; mix well. Add flour and 1/8 teaspoon salt, beating until smooth.
Dip eggplant in batter and brown on both sides in hot oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Combine cheese, parsley and pepper and mix well. Pour 1/2 cup Italian sauce on bottom of casserole dish.
Layer eggplant, some cheese mixture and repeat layers, finishing with sauce.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: pork tenderloin with garlic mustard sauce
directions: Mince garlic.
Slice scallion.
Cut pork into 8 diagonal slices.
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper and coat lightly with flour.
Heat oil and butter in a large frying pan over medium-high heat.
Add pork and cook until brown on each side about 3 minutes. Remove and cover to keep warm.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water, cornstarch and salt in pot and cook, stirring until thickened.
Add gelatin, vanilla and red coloring to first mixture.
Allow to cool.
Fold in 4 cups of fresh strawberries.
Pour into pie shells that have been dusted with powdered sugar to prevent sogginess.
Chill.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: old-fashioned peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook to soft ball stage. Add peanuts and cook until mixture turns dark.
Remove from heat. Add
baking
soda,
salt
and
vinegar; stir well. Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces. Yields 2 pounds.

title: ft.  leavenworth, kansas n.c.o.  club's salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shake well.
Makes a little over 1 quart.

title: amish roast for filling
directions: Mix all together and bake.
Makes enough for 30 people.

title: sophisticated succotash
directions: Blanch broccoli florets in large pot of boiling salted water until just crisp-tender, about 2 minutes.
Drain and immediately place in a bowl of ice water.
Drain and pat dry when cold.
Melt butter in heavy large skillet over medium heat.
Add carrots; cover and cook until crisp-tender, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes.
Increase heat to medium-high.
Add peppers; stir for 5 minutes.
Add squash; stir 1 minute.
Add lima beans, broccoli and salt.
Cover and cook until heated through, stirring occasionally, about 4 minutes.
Season with pepper.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Precook sliced potatoes and layer with onion.
Heat until smooth Cheez Whiz, cream of celery soup and milk.
Add to potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until thick and brown.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel, core and either chop or slice the apples.
Mix the apples, sugar, spices and butter together; set aside.
Roll out your pie dough and cut it into 4 or 5-inch squares.
Place the fruit mixture in the center of the square and bring the 2 opposite corners together over the fruit mixture.
Wet the tips of the pastry so that it will stick.
Do the same with the other 2 corners.
Do not seal all the edges or the steam will not be able to escape.
If you do, be sure to use a fork and make steam holes.

title: good cracker jack
directions: Pop the corn and set aside; do not salt.
Cook sugar, molasses, butter and vinegar until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Stir in soda and pour over popped corn.
Press into large, greased pan and allow to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Butter a 1-quart casserole.
Cook frozen broccoli 5 minutes and drain well.
Mix mushroom soup, mayonnaise, onion, American cheese and eggs.
Fold in broccoli; top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: blintzes
directions: Line pan with frozen blintzes.
Pour melted margarine over the blintzes.
In blender place sour cream, sugar and eggs and blend. Pour over blintzes and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: gooey caramel chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line 13 x 9 inch baking pan with foil. Combine flour, granulated sugar and salt in medium bowl; stir until blended. Cut in 14 Tbsp. (1 3/4 sticks) butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Press into bottom of prepared pan. Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned around edges. Remove pan to wire rack; cool completely. Combine 1 c. (2 sticks) butter, brown sugar and corn syrup in heavy medium saucepan. Cook over medium heat 5 to 8 minutes or until mixture boils, stirring frequently. Boil gently 2 minutes, without stirring. Immediately pour over cooled base; spread evenly to edges of pan with metal spatula. Cool completely. Melt chocolate in double boiler over hot (not simmering) water. Stir in remaining 2 Tbsp. butter. Pour over cooled caramel layer and spread evenly to edges of pan with metal spatula. Refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes or until chocolate begins to set. Remove pan from refrigerator; cool completely. Cut into bars. Makes 3 doz. bars.

title: orzo-stuffed tomatoes
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving:
Prepare orzo as directed, but do not salt water.
Meanwhile, cut a thin slice from stem end of each tomato; scoop out pulp and dice.
Place pulp in a 12 x 8-inch glass or ceramic baking dish; stir in sauce.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Mix cake as per directions on box.
Add creme de menthe to cake mix just before mixing time is up.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake as directed on box.
Cool completely.
Spread with chocolate topping and chill.
Mix 6 tablespoons creme de menthe with Cool Whip and spread on over chocolate.
Chill.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Shake chicken in flour, garlic salt, seasoned salt, paprika and dill in bag or bowl.
Brown chicken in oil.
Remove and arrange strips in single layers in shallow pan.
Blend wine, vinegar, brown sugar, ketchup and mustard and pour over chicken. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until glazed.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine corn and remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and bake in slow oven at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: that chip dip
directions: Mix liver sausage with sour cream; add Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Chill for several hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: garlic-parsley potatoes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; toss to coat well.
Layer half of mixture in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Sprinkle with half of parsley.
Layer remaining mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Uncover; sprinkle with remaining parsley.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: mostaccioli bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; add green pepper and onion. Cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water and seasonings.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer half the noodles, meat sauce and Velveeta cheese; repeat layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 6 to 8 servings.

title: frozen fruit delight
directions: Drain all fruit.
Bring sugar, flour and honey to a boil. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add 1/3 cup lemon juice into egg.
Add small amount of honey mixture.
Return to remaining mixture.
Bring just to boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Cool.
Stir in fruit.
Fold in whipped cream. Freeze firmly, 3 to 4 hours.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Combine flour and one cup sugar.
Slowly stir in milk.
Melt butter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Mix the peaches and the 1/2 to 1 cup sugar (to sweeten peaches to taste and depending on how sweet peaches are).
Spoon carefully over the batter.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: whoopy pies
directions: Mix together flour, soda, salt, cocoa powder and sugar.
Add egg, oil, vanilla and milk. Beat all together and drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet. Allow room for spreading. Bake 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli as directed.
Saute the onions in the margarine.
Add the flour and 1/2 cup water from the broccoli. Cook until thickened.
Blend in one 8 ounce jar Cheez Whiz.
Stir until smooth.
Mix the cooked, drained broccoli into this.
Add 3 beaten eggs.
Add the bread crumbs.
Mix all together.
Put into casserole dish.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, blend in sugar and flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in well greased pan.
Bank 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground meat and add taco seasoning.
Drain, then add remaining ingredients.
Let simmer for 1 hour.
Good served with rice or cornbread.

title: lemon buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Dissolve soda in hot water and add salt and lemon extract.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add flour to creamed mixture with buttermilk and beat until smooth.
Add the eggs last, all at once. Beat until very creamy.
Pour into a well greased and floured 10 inch tube pan.
I use Bakers Joy baking spray.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
While still warm, punch holes in cake with a toothpick.
Spoon lemon sauce over cake.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish. Cream powdered sugar, cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add milk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into prepared dish.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs and finely chopped peanuts over top.
Cover dish with plastic wrap or foil and freeze until firm.
This will keep for a long time.
Is so easy and so good.

title: beef marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Place meat in bowl and marinate overnight or up to 24 hours, turning occasionally.
If using fajitas, barbecue until well done.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry jello together.
Mix other ingredients and Cool Whip mixture.
Chill 1 hour.

title: surprise cheese puffs
directions: Allow cheese to remain at room temperature for at least 1 hour.
Blend in softened butter thoroughly; do not melt butter or cheese.
Add Worcestershire sauce, onion juice and hot sauce. Remove all crusts from bread loaf.
Cut lengthwise into 1 inch slices.
Spread top and sides with cheese mixture.
Cut into 1 inch strips.
Spread sides of strips with cheese; cut into 1 inch cubes.
Cover sides of cubes, leaving bottom uncovered.
Place carefully on cookie sheet so puffs do not touch; stack with wax paper between layers.
Place in freezer until puffs are frozen; store in plastic bags until needed.
Remove from freezer at serving time.
Place immediately in preheated 375° oven.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until corners are golden.
Serve at once. Yield: 80 to 100 pieces.

title: vegetarian low-fat baked beans
directions: In large pot, add drained beans, sauteed onion and bell pepper, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar and mustard. Place in large casserole dish and bake in 375° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: date bars
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy and light.
Add eggs and beat again thoroughly.
Add the flour and baking powder into this thoroughly, then fold in nuts and dates.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350° until top is brown, approximately 1/2 hour.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Hard-boil eggs.
Combine
cooked egg yolks with chopped pickles,
add 4 tablespoons of juice from pickles and crumbled bacon
and
mix
together.
Add
mayonnaise or salad dressing. Fill egg whites and sprinkle with paprika.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients in a bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in mixture of flour, soda and salt.
Add M&M's; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Sift together soda, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together sugars, eggs, shortening and pineapple.
Then add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well; drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: lumberjack steak marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate 2 pound beef loin for approximately 4 hours.
Cook about 20 minutes over hot charcoal.

title: hot cross buns(an easter favorite)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add butter, sugar and seasonings to scalded milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add one egg and one egg white to milk mixture; add yeast.
Beat.
Gradually beat in about 2 cups flour.
By hand, stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured pastry cloth.
Add raisins; knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in a buttered bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cream together sugar, oil add eggs.
Combine flour mixture and creamy mixture.
Shape dough into roll or log
and chill.
Slice dough into 1/4 inch thick slices and decorate with colored sugars.
Bake for 6 - 7 minutes.
Cool for 2 minutes and remove from cookie sheet.

title: mrs. carey's cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, butter and oil.
Add eggs, extracts and orange rind; beat well. Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Stir until blended.
Form dough into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until done.

title: cole slaw
directions: Wash and remove core from cabbage; cut into wedges and slice fine or use food processor until finely chopped. Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate overnight. Check seasonings before serving; can add more, if needed, according to taste.

title: nina's fluffy rice
directions: Place all ingredients in microwavable dish with tight fitting lid and place in microwave.
Cook on high power for 5 minutes.
Do not open container.
Then cook on 50 per cent power for 10 minutes.
Allow to set 5 minutes without opening.
Open, fluff, and serve.	Microwaves vary, so times may vary slightly.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Add to the eggs the oil, vanilla, brown sugar and bananas; beat well.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add wet and dry ingredients together and mix well. Add nuts.
Bake 1 hour or until done when tested at 325° in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
When done, remove from pans at once.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: spicy gazpacho
directions: Chop tomatoes, cucumbers, peppers and onions in a food processor until finely cut, but not pureed.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serves 8.
Contains 90 calories per 1-cup serving.

title: hot punch
directions: Mix and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Mix all ingredients except milk and boil until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Let cool.
Not cold.
Beat in milk until right thickness is attained.
Makes 1 Quart.

title: foil wrapped ginger chicken
directions: Flatten chicken.
Place each half on a piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil to enclose it.
Sprinkle chicken on both sides lightly with salt and pepper.
Combine onion, ginger, lemon juice, soy sauce and red pepper in small saucepan.
Heat, stirring, about 1 minute.
Spoon mixture over chicken halves evenly.
Close foil tightly.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In 2-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese and onions.
Spread salad dressing over onions, sealing to edge of bowl; cover.
Chill several hours or overnight. Garnish with bacon and shredded cheese if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops and put in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with rice.
Combine soup and water; pour over chops and rice.
Cover and cook about 1 hour at 350°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put all ingredients together and allow to come to boiling point. Add 1 gallon sliced pickles. Again allow to come to boil. Can. (Be sure to boil as it makes them soft.)

title: chicken piccata
directions: Place chicken breast between 2 pieces of plastic wrap.
Pound chicken to 1/2 inch thickness.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; coat with flour.
In a large skillet, brown chicken in 3 tablespoons butter 5 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from skillet.
Add remaining butter; cook mushrooms and garlic until tender.
Return chicken to pan.
Add wine and lemon juice.
Simmer 7 to 10 minutes.
Top with parsley.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oil. Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil or margarine and fry until golden brown, turning once.

title: pizza roll-ups
directions: Thaw dough.
Roll into 14 x 24-inch rectangle, about 1/4-inch thick.
Brown ground beef or turkey.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon filling evenly onto dough, slightly pressing filling into dough.
Roll dough lengthwise like a jelly roll and cut into 24 (1-inch) slices.

title: apricot bread pudding
directions: Place raisins and apricots in a bowl.
Cover with boiling water.
Soften 10 minutes; drain well.
Sprinkle half the fruit in the bottom of a buttered 8-inch square baking dish.
Butter bread and arrange, buttered side up, on top of fruit, overlapping, if necessary.
Sprinkle with remaining fruit.

title: chicken curry
directions: Saute in skillet the onion, butter, water and curry powder; set aside.
Mix all ingredients and serve on lettuce leaf and sprinkle with shredded coconut.

title: andes chocolate mint cookies
directions: Melt first three ingredients.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, stirring until melted.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill about 1 hour or until stiff enough to roll into balls.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Cookies are moist.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and set aside.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add water to juice to make 2 cups.
Bring to a boil and add Jell-O.
Add strawberries and stir until dissolved. Add pineapple and 1 cup cold water.
Put 1/2 in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Set.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and nuts. Spread on set Jell-O. Pour rest of Jell-O on top and let set.

title: mrs. kline's biscuits
directions: Pat out, don't roll, and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 375°.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Add pickles, eggs and celery and toss together lightly.
Add mayonnaise and blend.
Chill.
Serve on shredded lettuce.
Serves 8.

title: freezer bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers, onion and salt with a lid and let set for 2 hours.
Drain; add sugar, vinegar and seasonings.
Pour into containers and freeze.
Pickles are better if they are covered by the vinegar mixture.
They stay more crisp.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: chicken and scallops au gratin
directions: Season chicken and scallops with salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour.
Heat butter over high heat until hot and saute chicken and scallops 2 minutes.
Add shallots and mushrooms 1 minute.
Add wine and reduce sauce to 2 tablespoons.
Add cream and tarragon.
Cook 1 minute, stirring until sauce coats spoon.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon into ovenware and sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 375 ° for 5 minutes or until sauce is bubbly.
Serves 2.

title: biscuit mix
directions: With a pastry blender or 2 table knives, cut in shortening with other ingredients until the mixture resembles coarse meal. Store in airtight, covered containers.
This mixture will keep for some time on a cupboard shelf or for months if stored in the refrigerator.

title: easy beef roast
directions: Place in crock-pot and cook 5 to 6 hours on slow.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry sausage; drain grease.
Add vegetables; cook until tender. Add rice and soy sauce; salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry jam
directions: You will need plastic storage containers.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together thoroughly sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk, mashed bananas and flour.
Then stir in soda and fold in chopped nuts.
Bake in bread loaf pan 50 to 60 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder. Beat eggs thoroughly. Add oil and sugar; cream well. Add zucchini and vanilla, then add dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix well. Bake 1 hour in 325° oven. Makes 2 loaves.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Stir together in a medium bowl the mayo, Parmesan cheese and onion. Make sure artichoke hearts are very well drained (squeeze in paper towels) and chopped. Add to mayo mixture. Stir in lemon juice and black pepper. Scrape mixture into a small baking dish. Combine breadcrumbs and olive oil and sprinkle over dip. Bake at 400° about 20 minutes, until top is browned. Serve with crackers or crostini.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onion until done; drain and set aside.
Mix tomato paste and chili mix.
Cook 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Dip tortilla shell in sauce.
Put a tablespoon of meat and cheese.
Roll up tight.
Place seam side down.
Top with rest of sauce.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with rest of cheese.

title: applesauce cake(sugar-free)
directions: Soak raisins in 1 cup water until water is absorbed or evaporated.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Mix well. Blend in baking soda and stir well.
Add nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat the cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add milk; blend.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Put into a graham cracker crust and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: potato-leek soup
directions: In a large pot saute onions in oil
until clear.
Add water, salt, potatoes and leeks.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until potatoes are soft.
Puree in blender and return to pot.
Add milk. Heat for 5 minutes until hot.
Serve with croutons and fresh ground black pepper.

title: cheese logs
directions: With electric mixer, beat cream cheese, mayonnaise and milk until smooth.
Add Worcestershire sauce, onion and garlic powder; blend well.
Slowly add cheeses; combine thoroughly.
Shape into 2 logs 2-inches in diameter.
Combine parsley and wheat germ.
Roll cheese logs in parsley mixture to cover completely.
Wrap logs tightly in foil and chill thoroughly before serving with crackers. Makes 2 (1/2 pound) logs.

title: faith drobish's whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add honey, milk, oil and salt.
Add flour; knead 15 minutes.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Punch down; shape into 2 loaves.
Let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: children's play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, about 5 minutes, until it forms a ball.
Cool slightly and knead until smooth.
Store, wrapped tightly in plastic, in refrigerator. The dough hardens on standing.
Great for sculptures.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in pineapple and sprinkle blueberries.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, then cake mix.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix.
Add nuts, then sprinkle with remaining sugar. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Midway through baking, slice batter a couple of times.

title: lemon freeze
directions: Combine crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter in ice cube tray.
Mix well. Reserve 2 tablespoons of crumbs for topping. Press mixture with tablespoon until firm in tray.

title: poppy seed chiffon cake
directions: Stir
boiling
water
and
poppy
seed until smooth and cool. Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; make a
well and
add
in
order the Wesson oil, egg yolks, cooled poppy seed and vanilla.
Beat with spoon.
Into large bowl put egg whites and cream
of
tartar;
whip
until stiff.
Do not underbeat.
Pour egg
yolk
mixture
over
whites and fold in. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes, then at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together in large bowl and chill. Garnish with red and/or green cherries if desired.

title: hot seafood salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart buttered casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake in oven 350 degrees until bubbly.
About 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add refried beans, chili seasoning and water.
Simmer over medium heat for 10 minutes. Pour tomato sauce in plate.
Cover each tortilla in sauce one at a time.
Layer tortilla, then meat mixture and shredded cheese. Continue layering until all meat has been used.
Bake in a round covered dish or 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with your favorite Mexican toppings.

title: banana tree stumps
directions: In small saucepan, combine the butterscotch pieces and peanut butter.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted. Peel the banana and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Dip each piece of banana into the butterscotch mixture.
Lift out with a fork. Roll in the chopped nuts.
Place on waxed paper lined plate.
Chill for 2 hours.
Serves 2.

title: sausage and corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook sausage, onion and pepper until brown.
Drain sausage mix.
Add flour, tomato soup, salt and chili powder.
Add cheese and olives.
Put into 9-inch square pan.
Mix muffin mix as directed (on box).
Pour muffin mix over sausage mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and turn out.
Loosen edges.
Cornbread on bottom when turned out.

title: warm peach casserole
directions: In a slow oven at 300° to 325°, heat the peaches, juice and cinnamon sticks with cloves.
Heat about 1/2 hour.
Remove cinnamon sticks and serve in small dishes.

title: joanna's favorite chicken noodles
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Add salt and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Work fast and knead good.
Roll out thin on a floured surface.
Let dry for about 30 to 60 minutes.
Roll up like a jelly roll and cut as desired.
Unroll and let dry a while longer. Drop one at a time in boiling chicken broth and cook until done and not sticky in center of noodle.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bob and andy pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients. Add pecans and coconut; mix well. Pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add more flour if necessary to make a thick batter.
Drop by tablespoon into a hot, well oiled skillet.
Fry until golden.
Turn and brown other side.

title: ravioli and cabbage soup
directions: In a 5 to 6-quart pan, cook bacon over medium heat until translucent. Add onion; cook until onion and bacon are lightly browned (5 to 7 minutes). Stir in garlic and parsley. Add broth, water and carrots. Bring to a boil. Add separate ravioli to boiling broth. Reduce heat and simmer about 12 minutes (or follow ravioli cooking directions). Stir in cabbage during last 5 minutes.
Add cheese on top when serving. Serves 4 to 6.

title: hash brown cheese bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: In a large skillet cook and stir meats until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes and break up with fork.
Stir in tomato paste, garlic salt, oregano leaves and basil leaves.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes or until mixture is consistency of spaghetti sauce.

title: orange punch for 200("peach color")
directions: Add enough water to make 2 gallons to all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Dilute with ginger ale to serve, adding crushed ice to punch bowl.

title: cheese-onion casserole
directions: Put in buttered casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with bread crumbs, if desired.

title: bean broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the lima beans in microwave for 10 minutes with a little water. Drain. Add lima beans, broccoli and mushroom soup. Mix together well. Place in casserole dish. Top with onion rings. Bake 40 minutes to 1 hour at 350° or until onion rings are golden brown.

title: fat-free brownie oat cookies
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Mazola no-stick spray.
Combine flour, sugar, oats, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons onto prepared cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add next items.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, parsley and oregano.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours and serve.
If too thick or too rich, you can add bouillon or plain water.

title: blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in refrigerator.

title: nana's pumpkin bread
directions: Combine wet ingredients with dry ingredients.
Mix well. Grease loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix in flour (if glossy, add some flour).
Dough will be firm.
Roll in balls (about a teaspoon). Flatten and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
These can be decorated nicely for holidays with sugar sprinkles.

title: very moist gingerbread
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, molasses and buttermilk.
Combine flour, spices and salt. Dissolve soda in boiling water.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with soda water, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat well.
Pour batter into greased baking pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve while warm.
Serve with Cool Whip topping.
Yields 12 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake on large cookie sheet.
Mix pudding, milk and cream cheese together.
Put drained pineapple on cake, pudding on pineapple and Cool Whip on pudding.
Top with coconut and cherries.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Put shortening and margarine, water and cocoa in pan and bring to boil.
Pour over flour mixture.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix buttermilk, soda, vanilla and cinnamon in a cup.
Add to mixture.
Bake in a greased 12 x 18-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Spread apples in unbaked pie shell.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, and flour.
Pour over apples in unbaked pie shell.
Add butter to top of mixture.
Bake until apples are done.

title: people chow
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips in medium sized heavy saucepan over low heat; stir to blend.
Place cereal and nuts in large bowl.
Pour chocolate mixture over; mix until cereal and nuts are thoroughly coated.
Turn chocolate mixture into very large bowl or dishpan.
Sprinkle sugar over, 2 cups at a time, carefully folding and mixing until thoroughly coated.
Makes about 24 cups.

title: trail mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Store in an airtight container. Yield: 6 quarts.

title: mary viktorin's kolaches
directions: Warm milk, evaporated milk, sugar, oil, eggs and egg yolks, salt and vanilla and add to first mixture, beating well.
Add about 6 to 8 cups of flour, mixing well to make soft dough.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Cut off small portions of dough, using a tablespoon to form balls.
Place on a greased baking sheet about one inch apart and brush with melted butter.
Let rise until light, then make an indentation in each piece and place fruit filling therein.
If using cottage cheese as filling, be sure to enclose cheese in dough.
Spread out the small pieces of dough, place cheese on this and pinch all sides together to completely seal.

title: puppy chow snack mix
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips. Add peanut butter and mix well.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage; spread cheese over pie shell.
Spread sausage on cheese.
Beat eggs; mix with milk and pour over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frothy seas
directions: Combine juice concentrate, milk and ice cream in blender container. Blend 30 seconds. Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo.
Stir in eggs and cottage cheese.
Beat all into cornbread mix.
Add broccoli.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: double decker potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes. Do not peel.
Cut each potato lengthwise in 3 thick slices.
Place in baking dish, cut side up.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs; add pumpkin, sugar, salt, baking soda, flour and cinnamon.
Grease cookie sheet and line with wax paper.
Pour batter on wax paper and spread.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Place dish towel on counter; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Take roll out of oven; turn out on towel.
Remove wax paper using knife.
Roll up lengthwise (like a jelly roll) in dish towel. Cool 10 minutes.

title: broccoli rice cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Cook rice until tender; drain broccoli and mix with rice.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Heat to 350° until cheese is melted.

title: king ranch chicken #2
directions: Boil chicken.
Cool.
Remove meat from bones.
Reserve 1/2 cup broth.
Spray 9 x 13-inch casserole with Pam.
Tear tortillas into pieces.
Place in casserole.
Place chicken on top of tortilla pieces.
Puree tomatoes and liquid in blender or food processor.
In bowl, combine Ro-Tel puree, 1 cup cheese, cream of mushroom soup, black pepper and garlic powder.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle top with remaining 1 cup cheese.
Pour chicken broth over all.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add chocolate chips, nutmeats, marshmallow whip, vanilla and salt. Mix together; pour into buttered dish.
Makes 4 to 6 pounds.

title: cream of chicken
directions: Boil chicken in 2 cups water until cooked.
In large saucepan, melt butter; add flour and cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring.
Add 1 cup of broth used to cook chicken in.
Add as much milk as needed to make a medium sauce.
Add soup base or bouillon cube.
Bone and cut chicken meat into cubes; add to sauce.
Serve over mashed potatoes or biscuits; great with peas!

title: bride's pink punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Dissolve drink mix in cold water.
Add sugar and stir well.
Add pineapple juice and dissolved jello.
Refrigerate and add 7-Up and sherbet just before serving.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve plain or topped with whipped cream.
Refrigerate leftovers (if any).

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and milk in a heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Stirring constantly, bring the ingredients to a full boil for 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips and peanut butter gradually until melted.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Makes about 3 pounds of candy.

title: sunburst chiffon cake
directions: Measure the first 4 ingredients together; mix.
Make a well and add the next 4 ingredients.
In another large bowl, beat the egg whites and cream of tartar very stiff.
Pour egg yolks mixture gradually over beaten whites.
Fold in gently with rubber spatula. Pour into a 10-inch tube pan, ungreased.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes, then at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Turn pan upside down immediately.
Let cool, then remove.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Rinse, sort and cut the cranberries in half.
Chop nuts.
Set aside.
Melt butter and grate orange; set aside.
Sift together dry ingredients; set aside.
Combine beaten egg, orange juice and water, then stir in melted butter.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie pan.
Fry bacon and crumble into small pieces.
Put cheese, bacon and onion in pie plate.
Mix milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese, bacon and onion. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook slow for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Place in hot jars with sealed lids.
When you are ready to use, bring mixture to a boil and add 12 to 15 ounces of tomato paste.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: Chill and stir each time you use.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and keep in refrigerator.
The longer it sets, the better it gets.

title: egg beaters
directions: Mix thoroughly; 1/4 cup equals 1 egg.
If used for baking, add 1 teaspoon oil for each egg.
May be frozen.

title: chocolate sour cream frosting
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Beat in sour cream and salt. Makes 2 cups.

title: hot blue cheese tomatoes
directions: Cut top from tomatoes and crumble blue cheese over tomatoes. Lightly salt and pepper.
Bake in microwave on HIGH for 1 minute. Makes 4 servings.

title: christmas butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift and measure flour.
Add baking powder and salt.
Stir all together. Chill dough for a couple of hours for easier handling.

title: meatza pie
directions: Put meat, milk, bread crumbs and garlic salt in 9-inch pie plate.
Mix together with a fork. Pat mixture evenly onto bottom and sides of plate.
Spread tomato paste over meat.
Drain mushrooms and put over paste.
Top with Cheddar cheese and over this sprinkle oregano.
Sprinkle Parmesan over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until meat is done and cheese is lightly browned.

title: st. patrick's day salad
directions: Combine the first three ingredients and set aside.
Combine all the ingredients in order, then add the first mixture.
Pour into a ring mold and chill completely.

title: creole meat seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a large glass jar.
Seal tightly.
Keeps indefinitely.
Makes 3 cups

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Season chicken pieces.
Place all ingredients, except rice and peas, in pot.
Cover and cook for 2 hours on low heat.
Add rice and peas.
Cook for another 1 1/2 hours until tender.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Spread rice over bottom of shallow pan.
Place chicken on rice; season to taste and pour soup and milk (mixed together) over the chicken.
Bake in a 350° to 400° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Cover pan with foil before baking.

title: potato casserole
directions: Stir all together.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dot with butter and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: best salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar and pineapple.
Bring to boil; cool.
Mix cream cheese with pudding.
Combine the 2 mixtures and fold in 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Delicious.

title: red snapper on carrot,  orange, coriander salad
directions: Make salad and vinaigrette dressing.
In a nonstick pan, heat up a tablespoon of olive oil.
Dry snapper fillets with a tea towel and season with salt and pepper.
Place in the pan skin side down and cook on high heat until crisp, turn the heat down.
Cook until just soft in the center.
Remove and drain on a plate. Leave to rest 5 minutes in a warm place.	Boil potatoes.	Drain and toss with butter and parsley.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup, cheese and sour cream; heat in boiler until all mixed well and thoroughly heated.
Pour over mix in casserole. Sprinkle crackers and almonds over top of casserole.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add egg, milk, shortening and vanilla.
Mix only until all ingredients are blended.
Stir in dry blueberries.
(I use frozen berries without thawing.)
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate cream cheese pie
directions: Melt butter and mix well with graham cracker crumbs. Press into large pie pan to form crust. Separate egg whites from yolks (reserve yolks) and whip until stiff. Fold in 1/4 cup sugar. Set aside.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: greek island candy
directions: Melt butter and pour over nuts; set aside.
Mix together sugar, syrup, Pet milk and butter.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute. Add nut mixture.
Bring to a boil again and boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat, add vanilla and beat until gloss begins to leave and mixture thickens.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper to cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch.
Let boil.
When thick and clear, add jello. Cool a little.
Put strawberries in a baked pie shell.
Pour the cooled glaze over strawberries.
Put in refrigerator to cool.

title: mexican dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread it in ovenproof large pie plate. On it, spread chili peppers, olives and green onions.
Cover with cheese.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 325°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Boil 8 cups water;
add
pasta.
Reduce heat. Cook 8 to 10 minutes or until
tender.
Drain.
Add
pepperoni to pasta. Stir in pizza sauce.
Add
1 cup Mozzarella cheese, olives and Parmesan cheese.
Transfer to
a 12 x 7-inch baking dish, well buttered. Top with
remaining Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Prepare in large mixing bowl three and one-half cups of quick cook oats.
(Add one half cup nuts, if desired) and a pinch of salt.
Mix in a saucepan, one and a half cups of sugar, one stick of soft margarine, one-third cup of cocoa and one-half cup of milk. Mix well and bring to a boil, stirring to melt sugar nicely.
When this boils up, turn up heat; add two-thirds cup of peanut butter and two teaspoons of vanilla.
Stir until peanut butter is melted and well blended.
Pour this over the oats and nuts.
Stir with a fork until all oats are covered.
Drop on wax paper.
Let set to become firm.

title: peanut sticks
directions: Trim brown off bread (thick white bread).
Cut into 6 sticks. Bake 1 hour at 225°.
Now dip sticks in mixture.
Roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Repeat mixture if needed.

title: tex-mex
directions: Layer in the order listed; put in large Pyrex dish.
Serve with Frito chips or Tostito chips.

title: festive lasagne swirls
directions: Remove sausage from casings; crumble.
In large skillet, cook sausage; drain excess fat.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Simmer, covered, about 5 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak poppy seed in milk for 2 hours.
Cream butter.
Add sugar, milk and poppy seed.
Add dry ingredients, then egg whites. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: italian love cake
directions: Prepare marble cake mix as directed on package.
Put in oblong baking pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour on top of cake batter and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool before icing.

title: hawaiian ribs
directions: Brown ribs in heavy frypan or Dutch oven.
Combine cornstarch, molasses and soy sauce to make a paste.
Spread paste on both sides of each piece of ribs.
Rebrown quickly in hot fat.
Combine sugar, vinegar, water and pineapple juice; heat until sugar dissolves.
Pour over ribs.
Cover; cook 25 to 30 minutes.
Add pineapple chunks and green pepper cubes; re-cover and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Makes eight servings.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sour cream and oleo until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stuff celery with cheese mixture.
Makes 3 cups.
Can be refrigerated for a week.

title: witches hat surprise
directions: Set aside 1 3/4 cups of chocolate candies.
Place remaining candies in a large plastic bag.
Crush with rolling pin.
In a saucepan, combine crushed candies, milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until candies are melted and mixture is smooth.
Cool to room temperature.
Frost top of each cookie with 1 1/2 tablespoons of chocolate mixture.
Frost cones, leaving 1 inch at tip unfrosted.
Holding frosted cone by tip, fill each with 2 teaspoons candies; center filled one on top of frosted cookie to form "hat."
Place each hat on baking sheet.
Repeat until all cookies and cones are used.
Decorate witches hats with remaining candies.
Allow 15 minutes to set.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef with onion; add beans and heat.
Add sauce, shredded lettuce and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Add Doritos last. Garnish with cheese.

title: braised shrimp with vegetables(china)
directions: Remove shells and back veins from shrimp.
Cut broccoli into pieces.
Drain
mushrooms.	Cut whole bamboo shoots into thin slices.
Heat oil in wok over high heat.
Stir-fry shrimp in oil until tender, about 3 minutes.
Add broccoli to shrimp; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add mushrooms and bamboo shoots.
Stir-fry 1 minute longer.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over shrimp-vegetable
mixture.	Cook
and
stir until liquid boils. Cook and stir 1 minute longer.
Serves 4.

title: orange glow
directions: In 4-cup measure, combine all ingredients. Cover with plastic wrap and heat approximately 11 minutes.
After heating, release plastic wrap.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix crabmeat, 1/2 cup crumbs, eggs, mayonnaise, onion, parsley and salt.
Chill.
Shape mixture into 8 patties.
Coat each with remaining bread crumbs.
Fry in 1 1/2 inches of hot oil 5 to 7 minutes, or until golden brown, turning once.
Serve with tartar sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together.
Place in 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining chips. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: donna's dip
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Reserve liquid (add water to make 1/2 cup).
Combine all ingredients.
Run through blender; leave broccoli coarse.
Serve hot with vegetables and chips.

title: breakaway vegetable bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Dip each in butter and layer 1/3 into lightly greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 bacon, cheese, onion and pepper.
Repeat layers.
End with biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: coconut-lemon cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, beating until light and creamy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into 2 greased and floured cake pans and bake about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill and serve over salad.

title: beef brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat both sides of brisket with paprika. Heat oil in Dutch oven until oil is smoking.
Sear brisket on both sides.
Stir in ginger ale and soup mix.
Cover pot and cook in oven for 1 hour. turn meat over.
Cover pot and cook 1 more hour. Add potatoes and cook additional 45 minutes.

title: squash apple bisque
directions: Peel, core and chop apples.
Seed, skin and chop squash into small chunks.
Place chopped apples, squash, onions, chicken broth and rosemary in a pot and bring to a boil.
Reduce to a simmer and cook for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt margarine; cool.
Whisk in flour to make a roux.
Cook roux for 10 minutes or until it boils up a lighter color.
Pour cooked roux into vegetables and broth. Stir with a whisk to keep smooth.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add half and half to finished soup and serve.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: french creamy dressing
directions: Into mayonnaise, beat oil.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Put in covered jar; refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: lime salad
directions: Combine drained pineapple juice with enough water to make 1 cup.
Bring to a boil and dissolve the Jell-O in the hot juice mixture; cool.
Mash cream cheese, milk and pimentos; add pecans, pineapple and celery.
Stir into cooled Jell-O and pour into mold or an 8 x 13-inch pan.
Yield: 16 servings.

title: double peanut butter cookies
directions: In large bowl cream margarine, shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg.
Blend in flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir in chips.
Shape into 1-inch balls; place on cookie sheet.
Flatten in crisscross pattern with fork dipped in sugar. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Do not overcook squash; it should still be firm.
Melt butter and pour over the dressing in a large bowl. Toss to mix in butter, then reserve 1 1/2 cups for later.
Add all ingredients in a large mixing bowl (except reserved dressing). Turn into a buttered baking dish; sprinkle reserved dressing over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican party roll-ups
directions: In blender, combine the cream cheese, sour cream and picante sauce.
Blend until it is smooth with a creamy texture.
Spread the blended filling evenly on the open-face tortilla (you can decide how thick you want the filling to be to suit your personal taste).

title: cheesy buttons
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix and butter.
Stir in water and sesame seed until dough forms a ball.
Drop by scant teaspoonfuls into cheese (shaped into button shape, if desired). Coat balls with the cheese.
Place about 1-inch apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until golden 7 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: mark's favorite pasta salad (heart healthy)
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: buttermilk bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a heavy muffin tin.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 8 x 11-inch pan.
Spread cherry pie filling over bottom, then spread pineapple filling including juice over cherry filling.
Then spread cake mix evenly over fillings and add nuts. Melt margarine and pour evenly over mixture.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Bring 1 cup of soda almost to a boil; add to jello and stir. Add 1 cup cold soda.
Let jell some.
Add cherries.
Mix. Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: cheddar cheese sausage biscuits
directions: Mix all together, drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes or until brown. Yield, 72 small biscuits.

title: lemon mousse
directions: Mix by given directions.

title: sticky buns
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; let stand 1 hour, then add the next 6 ingredients.
Let rise 2 hours.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Spread dough with remaining ingredients.
Roll up dough like jelly roll and make 1-inch slices.
Put molasses in pan to cover bottom.
If you want, sprinkle with raisins and nuts.
Place dough slices in pan and let rise until double in size, about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Turn buns out on plate while still warm.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut
in Crisco or butter as for pie dough.
Stir in milk.
Sprinkle
a
surface lightly with flour and knead 20 to 25 times.
Divide
dough
in
half. Roll
or
pat half of dough into a
9-inch
round
cake
pan. Spread with melted butter.
Roll or pat
remainder of dough on top of butter.
Bake at 350° for 15
to
minutes
or until golden brown.
Remove and pour
sweetened, sliced strawberries on top and in center
of dough.
Serve with milk, ice cream or whipped cream.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken and Lipton onion soup.
Put into casserole dish.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Cover with foil. Do not look or peek.
Bake for 2 hours in 350° oven.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix crust ingredients together with a fork and blend.
Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake for 20 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine in blender and refrigerate.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, crumble bread.
Mix milk, sausage, eggs, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over bread.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Form into ball and roll in nuts.
Chill.

title: chicken cordon bleu in mushroom sauce
directions: Flatten chicken breasts.
Place 1 piece of Swiss cheese and 1 piece of ham on each chicken breast.
Roll up.
Secure with a toothpick.
Combine Oven Fry and parsley; set aside.
Dredge chicken in flour.
Combine egg and milk.
Dip chicken in egg/milk and roll in coating mix.
Brown lightly in skillet with small amount of oil.
Combine butter and mushrooms in lightly greased baking dish.
Arrange chicken over top.
Top with mushroom sauce. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Add wine to sauce. Mix well.
Spoon over chicken.

title: chicken-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Combine all ingredients except white sauce.
Place in buttered casserole. Pour white sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: oreo pie
directions: Layer in a deep dish as follows:

title: mamie's fudge
directions: Boil sugar, salt, butter and evaporated milk for 6 minutes. Put in large bowl chocolate bits, chocolate, marshmallow cream and nut meats.
Pour boiling syrup over ingredients in bowl; beat until chocolate is all melted and pour into a pan.
Let stand a few hours before cutting.
Store in a tin box.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake in 2 well-greased loaf pans 50 to 60 minutes. Bake both and freeze one for later. Serve warm with soft butter.

title: cheese blitzes
directions: Remove crusts from bread and roll each slice flat with rolling pin.
Mix rest of ingredients; spread on slices and roll.
Cut each roll in half.
Melt 2 sticks of butter or margarine.
Roll rolls in butter and then in a mixture of 1 cup sugar and 4 teaspoons cinnamon.
Freeze at this point, if desired, on cookie sheet and then store in freezer bag.
Remove when ready touse and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: black bottom cupcakes(makes 24)
directions: Combine in small mixing bowl, the first 3 ingredients.
Beat well and stir in chocolate chips; set aside.
Combine in a large mixing bowl, flour, cocoa, salt, sugar and soda.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: porcupine balls
directions: You season your meat with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
After that you roll meat into little balls, about 1/2 palm size, then roll little balls into rice until covered with white rice.

title: sweet 'n sour sauce
directions: Mix with first ingredients, boil until thick.
Good on fish.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Place in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
After 10 minutes cut to 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fire house fowl(better known as pigs and chickens)
directions: Cube the potatoes 1 inch square, slice green peppers lengthwise.
Slice the large onion lengthwise.
Dice the garlic and mix in a large bowl along with the peppers, potatoes, onion, oregano, basil and olive oil.
When well mixed, place in a large roasting pan.
Place the chicken and sausage evenly over the vegetables.
Cover with aluminum foil and place in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.
At 45 minutes, uncover and cook for 20 to 30 minutes more or until chicken and sausage brown.
Serves 6 to 8 firemen!

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Toss together with Italian dressing.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Store cocoa mix in an airtight container.
To serve, place 1/3 cup mix in a cup.
Add 1 cup boiling water and stir well.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cut fruit and nuts; dredge in flour.
Cream butter and sugar. Add well-beaten eggs and blend well.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Fold into butter and egg mixture.
Add extracts and mix well.
Add fruit and nuts and blend well.
Grease 10-inch tube pan.
Line with brown paper and grease again.
Pour batter into pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Cool in pan on cake rack.
Can be baked in 2 (5 x 3-inch) pans for 2 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli bread
